1
00:00:14,160 --> 00:00:17,800
The legendary search
for the next top models and actors

2
00:00:17,880 --> 00:00:21,440
that reshaped the Thai entertainment
and fashion industries is back.

3
00:00:21,520 --> 00:00:25,680
Join me, Kim Goodburn,
on this historic new journey.

4
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:28,600
This is<i> The Face Men Thailand Season 4.</i>

5
00:00:32,880 --> 00:00:36,400
<i>Last week, Team Mentor Off</i>
<i>proved their true potential</i>

6
00:00:36,480 --> 00:00:38,480
<i>during the dining table runway campaign.</i>

7
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:40,600
<i>Under the watchful eyes of celebrities,</i>

8
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:43,240
<i>they ultimately won the campaign.</i>

9
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:44,840
Bonus.

10
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:48,360
So this is what the smell
of a winner is like?

11
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:50,720
<i>Mentor Mile sent Jacob.</i>

12
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:53,880
<i>Meanwhile, Mentor Pancake</i>
<i>sent PP to the Black Room.</i>

13
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:56,400
I wasn't expecting them.

14
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:59,480
The one who should've been
in the Black Room is Lincoln.

15
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:00,680
My choice is set.

16
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:03,160
Because Gluf missed a challenge.

17
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:05,519
He had chickenpox back then, right?
Do you want to catch it?

18
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:08,200
Gluf has the right to everything,
but not the Final Walk.

19
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:10,120
Then why stay? Eliminate him.

20
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,720
<i>Regardless of who was sent,</i>

21
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:15,360
<i>Mentor Off eliminated both contestants</i>
<i>from the competition.</i>

22
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:16,840
Sorry.

23
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:18,800
Jacob, you might not be The Face yet.

24
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:19,920
Right.

25
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:52,960
<i>The winner</i>
<i>of </i>The Face Men Thailand Season 4

26
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:55,720
<i>will collaborate with Clear Thailand.</i>

27
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:59,880
<i>He will receive a one-year supply</i>
<i>of Clear Ice Cool Menthol.</i>

28
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:04,120
<i>And get the chance to work</i>
<i>with Vaseline Thailand.</i>

29
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:09,400
<i>Gluta Hyaluronic Acid,</i>
<i>Photoage Defense UV Serum</i>

30
00:02:09,479 --> 00:02:11,280
<i>free for an entire year.</i>

31
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:13,560
He will also collaborate with AXE.

32
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:16,760
<i>And receive a year's supply</i>
<i>of personal care products.</i>

33
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:20,240
<i>Bearbeary, only the wearers feel it.</i>

34
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:24,120
<i>Premium wear for every style,</i>
<i>featuring top design and innovation.</i>

35
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:26,360
<i>They'll award a 100,000-baht gift voucher.</i>

36
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:30,480
<i>Strive for perfection</i>
<i>with a membership to Hotman Fitness.</i>

37
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:33,320
<i>Including an 18-month</i>
<i>personal training program.</i>

38
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:37,320
<i>Plus a 200,000-baht package</i>
<i>from V Design Clinic.</i>

39
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,920
<i>Get ready to step onto the national screen</i>

40
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,960
<i>through a collaboration</i>
<i>with Channel 3 HD, Thailand.</i>

41
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:47,040
<i>And sign an acting contract</i>
<i>with Kantana Group Public Company Limited,</i>

42
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:49,640
<i>Thailand's leading producer</i>
<i>of dramas and films.</i>

43
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:56,600
Hello, everyone.

44
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,000
- Hello.
- Hello.

45
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:01,000
Welcome to week five of <i>The Face Men</i>.

46
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:03,640
We're past the halfway point,

47
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:05,680
and soon,

48
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:09,240
we'll find out
who the next The Face Men is.

49
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:11,320
Today's master class

50
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:14,120
is a crucial opportunity for you all

51
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:19,760
to learn acting
from two of Thailand's top actors.

52
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:22,720
Please welcome today's
master class instructors,

53
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,280
Mentor Ananda and Mentor Mile.

54
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:27,240
Hello.

55
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:29,720
- Hello.
- Hello.

56
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:33,560
It's amazing. Mile is a very famous actor.

57
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:37,480
And Ananda is already a legend.

58
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,960
He has been in so many films.

59
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:41,520
We're discussing acting today.

60
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,840
- When people watch a performance,
- Yes.

61
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:47,120
they often debate
if the acting feels real.

62
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:49,400
I want to ask Mentor Ananda,

63
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:52,440
what's the secret to not looking fake?

64
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:55,280
We've all watched films and felt…

65
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:58,720
"Why does that acting
feel so awkward?" Right?

66
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,800
Consider what makes acting feel fake.

67
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:04,680
Acting looks fake
when the motivation is wrong.

68
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:07,400
People catch on to that awkwardness.

69
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,640
The lines are right,
but it still feels off.

70
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:14,080
The scariest thing that leads to fakeness
is having an empty mind.

71
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:16,280
Your mind just goes completely blank.

72
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:18,200
- You get stressed and your face…
- Right.

73
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:20,040
You just end up frowning.

74
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:22,880
It's terrifying
to have nothing in your head.

75
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:27,040
If you understand your inner drive
at that moment, you can pull it off.

76
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:29,440
If you can't, it means you didn't prepare.

77
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:32,320
That carelessness is on you.
No excuse for that.

78
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:36,520
From my experience,
the most basic rule is to give it my all.

79
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:39,760
The character should feel truly alive.

80
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:43,840
I feel I both chose this
and was given the opportunity

81
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,680
when I played Kinn in <i>KinnPorsche</i>.

82
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:48,920
I learned through many different elements.

83
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:52,120
Realism finds its balance in the middle,

84
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:55,720
making it convincing
through natural desires.

85
00:05:55,800 --> 00:06:00,400
I believe
this is the foundation of acting.

86
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:03,840
I thought acting was easy,
but it's quite tough.

87
00:06:04,640 --> 00:06:07,240
Today, we'll focus on inner monologues.

88
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:10,080
We're using a scene from <i>Eternity.</i>

89
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,520
A scene I acted in myself.

90
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,520
It's one of my favorite scenes.

91
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,040
I want you all to try it.

92
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:20,800
So for today's workshop,
you'll all receive scripts from <i>Eternity.</i>

93
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:22,600
It's the story of Sangmong,

94
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,480
the nephew of the powerful Phapo.

95
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:27,520
However, Sangmong falls in love
with Yupadee,

96
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,600
Phapo's wife.

97
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:34,120
When Phapo finds out the truth,
he decides not to kill Sangmong.

98
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:37,960
Instead, he chains them together
for the rest of their lives.

99
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:40,160
This turns their love into hatred

100
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:42,440
and eventually drives them mad.

101
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:46,720
All right. Are there any special rules
for this workshop, Mentor Ananda?

102
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:50,960
The script is quite basic.
Don't worry about it.

103
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:55,440
Focus on what we discussed today
about inner drive.

104
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:59,240
I want to see your interpretation
and how you become the character.

105
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:02,280
Honestly, I think it's hard for everyone.

106
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:06,200
We only have ten minutes to prepare.
Not enough time to explore.

107
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:08,600
We can't build anything.
We just have to do it.

108
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:12,240
For the first team,
who will play Sangmong?

109
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:13,200
He's first.

110
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,280
- Leo.
- Leo.

111
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:19,920
- Wait, I'm not done yet.
- There you guys go again.

112
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:21,800
Who's going to be Yupadee?

113
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:25,080
I've only taken one acting class,
and I want to test myself.

114
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:27,120
Since I have a short attention span,

115
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:29,160
I need something more challenging.

116
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,760
So I'll just lie down.

117
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:37,280
A Korean meets a Thai.

118
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:39,440
As if he just returned from war and died.

119
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:42,360
The Korean arrives through
Doraemon's door and finds him.

120
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,560
Yupadee.

121
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:48,880
Yupadee.

122
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:51,920
I love you.

123
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:55,960
This feels exactly like a Korean drama.

124
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:58,800
If Thailand needs
a new Korean drama actor,

125
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,640
this <i>oppa </i>is the one.

126
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:03,200
We will stay together like this.

127
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,040
For all…

128
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,040
eternity.

129
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:11,720
I didn't understand,
but the vibe was right, and he was hot.

130
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,640
If I were the dead person there,

131
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:16,320
I would wake up
and I would come back to life.

132
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:18,080
I'd come back just to kiss <i>oppa</i>.

133
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,920
Monologues are tough.

134
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,400
It was okay. But Peem and I wanted to try.

135
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:25,560
Yes, that's fine. I'm okay with anything.

136
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:31,760
I mixed mud with water to wipe your body.

137
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:34,520
Just like you did for me.

138
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:37,159
So you can feel refreshed

139
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,480
and relaxed.

140
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:41,520
You'll sleep peacefully.

141
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,240
Gluf probably studied acting a bit.

142
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,240
You could see how he immersed himself.

143
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:49,960
His starting point was good,
but he lost momentum midway.

144
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:52,960
We need to establish some shared history
between the characters.

145
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:55,320
- Our characters, our relationship.
- Right.

146
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:59,080
When we face something like this,
it's easier to tap into those emotions.

147
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:03,320
Instead of trying to tell yourself,
"love her" or "be sad."

148
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:04,600
No need to say it.

149
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:06,880
It'll naturally come through
and stay with you.

150
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:09,280
Okay. It's not bad today.

151
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:11,120
I did okay,
but there's still room to improve.

152
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,320
I…

153
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:15,000
fell in love with you

154
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,800
from the very first second…

155
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,720
that I…

156
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:25,080
laid eyes on you.

157
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:31,160
When I tried playing Sangmong,
I felt that Yupadee was my lover.

158
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,600
I knew right then

159
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:36,920
that we would be together…

160
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,760
for all eternity.

161
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:41,360
- He was good.
- Good. It was enjoyable.

162
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,680
It was relaxed.

163
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:46,560
He started off feeling love
and appreciation for her presence.

164
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:48,080
I could feel that from here.

165
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:50,640
Through his smile and overall expression.

166
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:53,520
I liked how Kimhan interpreted it.

167
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,240
You could see the dynamic
of him being in that moment.

168
00:09:56,320 --> 00:10:00,560
To me, that feels like the main goal
of this opening scene.

169
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,240
I…

170
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,960
loved you from the very first second.

171
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:10,960
Today, I tried to provide
a tangible version of the theory,

172
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:12,280
so you can apply it.

173
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:15,560
It's difficult.
No one did exceptionally well yet,

174
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:17,120
but I can see their determination.

175
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:20,480
It's clear that with more time,
they would perform better.

176
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:23,400
Everyone has learned about acting now.

177
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:26,200
I hope you can all apply these skills

178
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:28,040
in today's challenge.

179
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:31,400
If you're curious, let's meet the person
presenting the challenge.

180
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,880
Please welcome Cindy.

181
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:37,280
- Hello.
- Hello.

182
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,720
SIRINYA BISHOP

183
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:40,880
MODEL, ACTRESS, HOST,
AND WOMEN'S RIGHTS ACTIVIST

184
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:45,840
Today's challenge is called
"Heroes vs Villains."

185
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:51,480
This challenge will test
your acting skills

186
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:53,240
because we're doing a photoshoot.

187
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:58,720
Everyone will have to play
both hero and villain in the same photo.

188
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:02,000
For this photoshoot,
everyone gets two sets.

189
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:03,560
One minute per set.

190
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:08,360
In the first set, you'll play a hero.

191
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:12,360
In the second set,
you'll switch to a villain.

192
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:15,040
Changing facial expressions is fine.

193
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:17,440
But if posing is required, I'm screwed.

194
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:18,600
It's not a big deal.

195
00:11:18,680 --> 00:11:21,760
I think I can handle it.

196
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:25,160
The photographer
for our master class today…

197
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:27,400
Please welcome Tim Phansiri.

198
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,720
Let's go.

199
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,760
- Hello.
- Hello.

200
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:33,640
PHANSIRI SIRIVEJCHAPHAN
THAILAND'S LEADING FASHION PHOTOGRAPHER

201
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:37,080
Today, we'll be shooting
the main character posters

202
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:39,560
for a serial killer movie.

203
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:41,320
You'll have two personalities.

204
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:45,760
One is a good person,
and the other is a serial killer.

205
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:49,000
You must bring out
your inner ruthlessness.

206
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,600
The two sides must completely contrast.

207
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:54,840
I want to see the emotional depth
you can portray.

208
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:57,680
Playing a killer
doesn't exactly suit my look.

209
00:11:57,760 --> 00:11:59,040
But I'll give it a try.

210
00:11:59,120 --> 00:12:02,600
I'll see how to act like a killer.

211
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:05,480
What are the judging criteria, Tim?

212
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:06,600
Make me feel it.

213
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:10,320
Once I feel you can clearly convey it,

214
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:12,920
whether it's the good guy's emotions

215
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,120
or the villain's emotions,

216
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:16,320
without being fake.

217
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,000
Yes. That's the challenge.

218
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:20,040
Is it my thing? Not really.

219
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,880
But I love anything dramatic.

220
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,520
I think I can do it.

221
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:28,440
I just want to say
you have to win this master class.

222
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:31,680
Because the benefit
will affect the campaign.

223
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,920
And don't forget.

224
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,000
For the team that loses the campaign,

225
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:40,800
your mentor can send more than one person
to the Elimination Room.

226
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:46,840
The winning mentor can eliminate
more than one person too.

227
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:51,440
Now I'm scared.
There won't be anyone left on the show.

228
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:54,360
I'm confused.
Why would a mentor send two people?

229
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,240
As options for the other mentor?

230
00:12:57,880 --> 00:12:58,720
It's weird.

231
00:12:58,800 --> 00:12:59,800
All right, everyone.

232
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:01,960
You've heard the special rules, the brief,

233
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:04,040
and the judging criteria.

234
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:06,040
Now, please get ready.

235
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,560
- Yes.
- Get ready.

236
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:11,680
So ready.

237
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:13,760
We already have this in the bag.

238
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:16,680
If not, we'll deal with it later.

239
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:20,000
I'll do my absolute best.

240
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,640
I will give it my all today.

241
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:24,760
We have to win this master class.

242
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:27,520
Because there are only three of us left.

243
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:30,080
We can't afford to lose anyone else.

244
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:39,960
Welcome back to our master class today.

245
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:43,200
Under the concept Heroes vs Villains.

246
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,360
For today's master class,

247
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:48,680
the contestants must portray
different characters

248
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:51,160
within a single photoshoot.

249
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:55,880
Now, if everyone is ready.
Let's meet our first contestant.

250
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,560
Please welcome Kimhan.

251
00:13:58,120 --> 00:13:59,680
- Come on.
- Let's go.

252
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:02,960
Hello, Tim. Hello.

253
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:05,600
I'm glad I'm not the last one anymore.

254
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:08,440
I'm always last.
I want to watch the others for once.

255
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:13,960
We'll start with the hero theme.
You have one minute.

256
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:17,000
Then we'll shoot the villain theme.

257
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:19,560
If you're ready, one minute starts now.

258
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:22,640
- Keep going.
- Okay.

259
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:24,240
Interesting.

260
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:27,600
- Good.
- My concept is pretty straightforward.

261
00:14:27,680 --> 00:14:30,640
My reference is Clark Kent, Superman.

262
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:34,240
He's the most relatable superhero.

263
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:36,440
- Tuck your chin. Great.
- 30 seconds.

264
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:37,600
Use your eyes, Kim.

265
00:14:37,680 --> 00:14:40,200
- Give me a good guy vibe.
- You're in a good mood.

266
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:43,720
- Still a good guy.
- Yes, good. Interesting.

267
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:44,880
Ten seconds left.

268
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:46,560
- Eight, seven…
- Hand down.

269
00:14:46,640 --> 00:14:51,240
I have to praise Kimhan for his design.
He would give everything a shot.

270
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:53,760
He wore glasses, then took them off.

271
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:57,040
And he controlled
his facial expressions well.

272
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:59,760
Now we'll shoot the villain theme.

273
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:02,040
If you're ready, one minute starts now.

274
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:03,120
That's it.

275
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,640
It gives off Joker-like vibes.

276
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:08,800
The most iconic villain is the Joker.

277
00:15:08,880 --> 00:15:09,720
My plan was

278
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:12,480
to smile, but make it look different.

279
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:16,480
Mix in some ruthless inner emotions.

280
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:18,440
- Hey. That's enough.
- No.

281
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:23,280
Wait, I heard the mentoring time was over?

282
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:25,320
- The coaching was done.
- No, I…

283
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:27,040
- Twenty seconds left.
- Wasn't it?

284
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:31,120
I might've been a bit biased.
If no one stops me, I'll just play dumb.

285
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:33,520
Ten seconds left.

286
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,600
Seven.

287
00:15:34,680 --> 00:15:36,400
- Give me a serious one.
- Six, five.

288
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:40,320
Four, three, two, one.

289
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:42,720
I think for the hero part,

290
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:45,040
there's less variety than the villain's.

291
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:49,560
He showed a wider range
of expressions as a villain.

292
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:50,760
I like the creativity.

293
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:54,520
I like that he planned his character well.

294
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:58,880
It's obvious his hero
and villain personas were distinct.

295
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:01,280
He did a really good job.

296
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:02,720
I think it turned out well.

297
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:05,440
Let's meet our second contestant.

298
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:06,720
Let's welcome Manyoo.

299
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:10,160
Going second…

300
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,400
I usually go last.

301
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:14,520
Finishing early means
I get to watch everyone else.

302
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,200
It felt a bit weird.

303
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,680
You may start.

304
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,720
Good. Keep going.

305
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:21,360
For my hero, I felt like…

306
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:24,680
I wanted to tell a story through my eyes.

307
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:27,400
Because I don't think
I'm very good at acting.

308
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:30,320
Still, I tried my best.

309
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:32,240
Would it be better with more variety?

310
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:34,200
Hey, no need to overdo it.

311
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:36,560
Let's just try.

312
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:38,120
- We're still on the hero.
- Good.

313
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:41,000
Manyoo had smiling eyes.

314
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:45,040
He naturally has a friendly face.

315
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:48,600
But from certain angles,
he looked quite masculine.

316
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:51,920
Next up is the villain theme.

317
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,080
Action!

318
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:54,160
Good.

319
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:56,200
- More intense.
- That's it.

320
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:59,800
I actually prefer
his villain portrayal over his hero.

321
00:16:59,880 --> 00:17:04,240
Some shots showed a hint of torment.

322
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:05,560
Did you notice that?

323
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:07,000
So evil.

324
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:09,640
Pure evil. So wicked.

325
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:11,800
Let's move to the next contestant.

326
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:13,200
Let's welcome Rome.

327
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:17,119
Since his mentor isn't here,
should we tease him?

328
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:19,480
- Calm down, Ananda.
- Don't face the camera.

329
00:17:19,560 --> 00:17:21,720
- Don't show his face. It's unique.
- No!

330
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:25,119
I was nervous.
The time limit on set is stressful.

331
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:28,079
I just tried to stay
as relaxed as possible.

332
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,120
You may start.

333
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:32,720
He gives off a Keanu Reeves vibe.

334
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:34,360
The hero, right?

335
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:37,280
I figured it should be
friendly and approachable.

336
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,840
Ready to help.

337
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:41,040
Kind of like Superman.

338
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,920
Yes, always smiling.

339
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:47,240
One minute left for the villain theme.

340
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:49,320
If you're ready, start the clock.

341
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,720
The other part?

342
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,760
It was the villain part, right?

343
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:55,640
I imagined myself as a psychopath.

344
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:57,280
Like Jack the Ripper.

345
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:59,120
But I'm not sure if I nailed it.

346
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:02,360
Rome gave off strong model vibes.

347
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:04,640
But being a model has its downside.

348
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:07,040
He shows a limited range
of facial expressions.

349
00:18:07,120 --> 00:18:08,800
Next up is Mew.

350
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,040
Start the clock.

351
00:18:10,120 --> 00:18:12,600
- Give me the good guy.
- Good guy. Hero.

352
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:15,160
- This is the good guy.
- Good guy first.

353
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:17,680
He always serves face.

354
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:20,160
Mew started with a fierce stare.

355
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:23,240
And the intensity just kept rising.

356
00:18:23,320 --> 00:18:24,600
So there's no compromise

357
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:28,400
with the image of a smiling savior.

358
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:30,440
One thing everyone agreed on

359
00:18:30,520 --> 00:18:32,200
was that he looked evil to his core.

360
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:35,240
Personally, this hero is definitely here
to scam people.

361
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:37,360
I've officially served good guy energy.

362
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:39,960
That was all I had.
That was all of me, period.

363
00:18:40,040 --> 00:18:41,160
- His model looks.
- Yes.

364
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:45,120
Very model-like.
That's why every photo was fierce.

365
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:48,240
For the hero theme,
he needs to look nicer.

366
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:50,720
Of course. Is it wrong to look fierce?

367
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:55,000
My face card serves fierceness.
No plastic surgery. Completely natural.

368
00:18:58,360 --> 00:19:00,280
Now switching to the villain look.

369
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:02,280
One minute. Start the clock.

370
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:05,880
Suddenly masculine.

371
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:08,520
- Hey, that wasn't bad.
- That's it.

372
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:10,280
I cannot force a smile.

373
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:12,520
When I smile, it looks fake. Yes.

374
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:13,840
It's just fake.

375
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:16,640
But portraying arrogance?
Yes, that's my forte.

376
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:19,640
Let's welcome the next contestant, Leo.

377
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:21,680
I'm confident.

378
00:19:21,760 --> 00:19:23,680
- Confident?
- I'm confident.

379
00:19:26,480 --> 00:19:27,320
Good.

380
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:32,080
- Make me feel it.
- He keeps smiling.

381
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:33,920
I need more variety.

382
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,600
I think he interprets it
simply as being a good guy.

383
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,240
That a hero is a good guy.

384
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:42,760
But when I think of a hero,
it's about confidence and strength.

385
00:19:44,520 --> 00:19:49,080
I guess Leo was trying
to build up his emotions.

386
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:52,840
I could see that,
but there was very little variety.

387
00:19:58,560 --> 00:19:59,840
- That's it.
- That's it.

388
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:01,400
Okay.

389
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:06,840
Just swear! Let it out!

390
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:08,480
Fuck!

391
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:11,400
At first, I heard an F-word.
Leo, no. You can't say that.

392
00:20:12,520 --> 00:20:14,840
- That's it.
- Oh, that was Korean.

393
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:15,800
Fuck, okay.

394
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:20,240
Okay, good.

395
00:20:21,680 --> 00:20:24,400
The emotion wasn't clearly
shown in his eyes.

396
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:26,120
He just looked handsome.

397
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:32,120
So I don't see a clear difference
between his hero and villain portrayals.

398
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:34,040
Let's move on to the next contestant.

399
00:20:34,120 --> 00:20:35,280
Lincoln, please.

400
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,720
So handsome and cool.

401
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:41,280
- Already?
- Yes.

402
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:48,120
Honestly, at first, I wanted
to keep it relaxed and neutral.

403
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:51,280
I just wanted one shot like this.

404
00:20:57,400 --> 00:21:01,160
There was barely any variety.
Just one expression.

405
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,960
And it was pretty boring.

406
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:07,240
For Lincoln,
I think his villain shot was better.

407
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:11,680
I could feel a level
of destructive energy from it.

408
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:14,600
Sometimes photography
relies on composition.

409
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:16,240
It's also driven by inner emotion.

410
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:19,920
This round should be about emotion,
but I didn't see much of it.

411
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,400
Gluf, you're next.

412
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:24,040
Hello.

413
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:26,160
Time starts now.

414
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:31,000
Everything happened so fast
and I didn't have time to think.

415
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:33,680
I went in and started shooting.
I couldn't think clearly.

416
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:35,560
Now for the villain set.

417
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:37,360
One minute. Go.

418
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:41,280
- Use your hands, it's fine.
- Forty seconds.

419
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:43,400
Feel it. Use your whole body.

420
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:47,760
I don't think he showed much variety,
although he has a unique face.

421
00:21:47,840 --> 00:21:49,800
Gluf is in the same category as Rome.

422
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:52,360
His photos might turn out
better than expected.

423
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:55,120
Because of his face.
The distinctiveness of his face…

424
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:57,760
might make it seem like
there's more of a story

425
00:21:57,840 --> 00:22:01,440
than there actually was.
But his eyes lack emotional expression.

426
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:03,880
Next up, Peem.

427
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:06,760
If you're ready, time starts now.

428
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:10,080
His eyes are a bit stiff.

429
00:22:10,160 --> 00:22:12,400
He was tense and nervous, so it felt off.

430
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:14,680
You need to relax more.

431
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:17,320
Relax. Try smiling with your teeth
for a few shots.

432
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:20,160
- I feel like he's tense…
- He was tense and nervous.

433
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:22,880
And having only one minute
makes it difficult.

434
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:24,160
Stiff eyes again.

435
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:26,080
I just didn't realize it.

436
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:31,200
My hero set wasn't that great.
My eyes still looked stiff.

437
00:22:31,280 --> 00:22:34,280
Next up is the villain photo set.

438
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:36,840
Peem, take a deep breath. Relax.

439
00:22:36,920 --> 00:22:38,720
- Okay.
- Stretch a bit.

440
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,800
Stay relaxed, then give it your all.

441
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:44,440
Let's do this. Come on.

442
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:46,640
Ready? Time starts now.

443
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:48,800
- Don't hold back. Let it out.
- Good.

444
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:50,280
Use your voice, your hands.

445
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:52,160
Yes, good.

446
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:53,920
It was obvious.

447
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,560
He's getting better
at escalating the story.

448
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:59,920
He showed a lot of expression
in the villain part.

449
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:02,960
And he had better control
of his expressions and poses.

450
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:05,400
I felt like I was more relaxed.

451
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:08,000
I think I did well on this one.

452
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:10,360
I'm just waiting to see how it turns out.

453
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:11,960
How it turns out.

454
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:13,680
Next up, Bonus.

455
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:16,040
When it comes to photoshoots,

456
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:19,520
since master class one, two, and three,
I've messed up every time.

457
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:23,680
I would probably mess up this one too.
So I just went for it. Let's go.

458
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:28,120
Try to make us believe you're a good guy.

459
00:23:28,760 --> 00:23:31,840
- Convince me.
- Believe in yourself.

460
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:35,320
Honestly, you don't come across
as a good guy right now.

461
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,320
Convince me.

462
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:37,760
Oh, poor thing.

463
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:39,400
His face just doesn't look…

464
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:41,520
He looks unfriendly,
though he isn't a bad guy.

465
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:43,520
But he's cute when he smiles.

466
00:23:45,120 --> 00:23:46,640
Good guy.

467
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:53,160
It's just how my face looks.
I don't look like a good guy, so I smiled.

468
00:23:53,240 --> 00:23:56,360
Telling myself, "I'm a good guy."
My face just looks like this.

469
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:58,080
What can I do? It's just my face.

470
00:23:58,160 --> 00:24:02,080
- Next up is the villain shoot.
- Let's go!

471
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:04,720
Okay.

472
00:24:08,040 --> 00:24:10,760
- Just listen to Tim.
- Start the clock.

473
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,560
I really enjoyed it.

474
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:15,640
It might not fit the brief
which required a serious tone.

475
00:24:15,720 --> 00:24:18,760
But if I were too serious,
I'd be too stiff like last time.

476
00:24:18,840 --> 00:24:20,160
I was too stiff before.

477
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:21,840
I did the exact opposite now.

478
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:24,760
Maybe in this master class,
I'll find the right balance.

479
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:27,320
Next up, Donut.

480
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,880
One minute on the clock. Go.

481
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:29,880
Come on.

482
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:32,720
Playing the villain was manageable.

483
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:35,160
But playing the good guy was kind of hard.

484
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:38,760
Do you have to smile that much?

485
00:24:38,840 --> 00:24:41,240
Don't forget, good guys can be cool too.

486
00:24:41,320 --> 00:24:44,480
I heard him say that
good guys can keep a straight face.

487
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:47,120
I did that, and my photos turned out well.

488
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:49,320
Next up, the villain shoot.

489
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:50,920
You may begin.

490
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:54,160
Good.

491
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,400
Good.

492
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:58,720
He portrays the villain so naturally.

493
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:03,440
Yes, why does he look so natural?

494
00:25:03,520 --> 00:25:05,480
Donut is cheating by using his tattoos.

495
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:08,160
If I had a tattoo, I'd show it too.
But if I show mine…

496
00:25:09,920 --> 00:25:10,880
It's a heart.

497
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:12,280
Bring it.

498
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:13,840
- That's it.
- Forty seconds.

499
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:15,280
Good.

500
00:25:15,360 --> 00:25:16,480
- Bring it!
- True colors.

501
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:17,880
His true colors.

502
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:20,680
I couldn't picture it in my head.
So I used my voice.

503
00:25:20,760 --> 00:25:22,560
It kind of unlocked something in me.

504
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:25,400
I pushed past my limits.
I've never done this before.

505
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:28,800
- Three, two, one.
- Look evil. Yes.

506
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:30,040
Time's up.

507
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:33,920
Donut is my top pick right now.

508
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:35,080
With his emotions,

509
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:38,920
the feelings conveyed in his photos
tell the best story.

510
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:40,960
The last person for this master class.

511
00:25:41,040 --> 00:25:42,120
Let's welcome Pom.

512
00:25:43,960 --> 00:25:47,520
My plan was exactly this.
Give them a hero look,

513
00:25:47,600 --> 00:25:48,560
then a villain look.

514
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:50,480
I just stuck to my plan,

515
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:52,080
and focused entirely on Tim.

516
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:53,360
Start the clock.

517
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:55,200
Slowly build up the emotion, Pom.

518
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:58,000
Convey that you're a kind guy first.

519
00:26:00,120 --> 00:26:01,800
He's the only one

520
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:06,120
who didn't interpret a hero
as someone with a bright smile,

521
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,840
which is interesting.

522
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:09,680
All of Pom's work is great.

523
00:26:09,760 --> 00:26:13,600
He's interesting
and intimidating in this competition.

524
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:19,000
Pom's photos
represent everything quite perfectly.

525
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:22,440
Okay, next up is the villain set.

526
00:26:22,520 --> 00:26:23,480
Start the clock.

527
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:28,160
He has great control
over his facial expressions.

528
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:31,400
Pom is already great at what he does.

529
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:32,320
He never misses.

530
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,200
He's a pro.

531
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:36,240
He's a mentor favorite.

532
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:39,480
Just now, all 11 contestants

533
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:42,400
brought to life
their Heroes vs Villains looks

534
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:43,800
and completed the shoot.

535
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:47,520
Now, let's hear
from our judges and mentors.

536
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:48,800
Let's start with Cindy.

537
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:54,000
Overall, it was very interesting.

538
00:26:54,080 --> 00:26:59,320
But overall, I'd like everyone to focus
a lot more on your acting classes.

539
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:02,560
In the entertainment industry,
whether in fashion

540
00:27:02,640 --> 00:27:04,600
or elsewhere,

541
00:27:04,680 --> 00:27:07,000
acting plays a crucial role.

542
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:09,800
So, please go back and do your homework.

543
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:12,040
From what I saw, looking fierce is easy.

544
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:16,680
But when you have to sell a product
with genuine happiness and a good heart,

545
00:27:16,760 --> 00:27:18,360
why does it become so difficult?

546
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:20,480
Develop your inner self

547
00:27:20,560 --> 00:27:23,520
to truly convey
different levels of emotion.

548
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:26,320
What's missing today is the story.

549
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:29,160
I think many of you made the mistake of

550
00:27:29,240 --> 00:27:32,520
trying to add emotion by…

551
00:27:34,600 --> 00:27:36,280
But that should come from within.

552
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:38,320
Instead, you projected it outward.

553
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:39,360
You just screamed.

554
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:42,520
You need to show that drive in your eyes.

555
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:44,280
Believe it or not, that intensity

556
00:27:44,360 --> 00:27:47,640
in your eyes is stronger
than any facial expression.

557
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,520
I'm very surprised.

558
00:27:49,600 --> 00:27:52,200
Surprised that
when you put it all together,

559
00:27:52,280 --> 00:27:53,720
the competition is so close.

560
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:55,680
Much closer than I initially thought.

561
00:27:55,760 --> 00:27:57,000
But all in all, yes.

562
00:27:57,080 --> 00:28:01,280
If you can deliver
what the brief asks for,

563
00:28:01,360 --> 00:28:05,120
which is the hero's inner self
through your eyes,

564
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:07,560
it would be much more dynamic.

565
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:09,320
And a lot more fun.

566
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,480
Wow, I'm so surprised.

567
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:14,080
Everyone's final photos
are unexpectedly good.

568
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:16,400
There are so many strong shots,
it's hard to choose.

569
00:28:16,480 --> 00:28:20,480
Now, let's look at the top three photos…

570
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:23,760
from today's
Heroes vs Villains master class.

571
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:30,920
When I saw Manyoo on set, I felt nothing.

572
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:35,320
I thought he was too stiff,
but looking at the photo Tim chose…

573
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:36,640
there's a certain impact.

574
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:39,680
The reflection in his eyes
shows the magic of photography.

575
00:28:39,760 --> 00:28:41,640
Can I just give all the credit to Tim?

576
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:44,760
Let's hear the comments for each photo.

577
00:28:45,320 --> 00:28:46,200
- Cindy.
- Yes?

578
00:28:46,280 --> 00:28:48,160
What do you think of Kimhan's photo?

579
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:52,200
To me, Kimhan is the only one
who clearly delivered a story.

580
00:28:52,280 --> 00:28:56,360
His character is very clear.
He was focused and stayed in character.

581
00:28:56,440 --> 00:29:00,640
The final result has a strong impact.

582
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:02,400
It's really good.

583
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:04,920
The second photo is Pom's.

584
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:06,400
It really stands out.

585
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:09,560
Looking at this final photo
from an audience's perspective…

586
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:12,480
I think he embodies the hero the most.

587
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:14,200
He's the best among the three.

588
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:18,720
He balances the hero and villain
perfectly in one shot.

589
00:29:20,200 --> 00:29:22,760
Now for the final photo, Manyoo's.

590
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:25,400
From what I've seen of your progress,

591
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:27,080
you really stood out today.

592
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:30,240
One thing I love is your emotional range.

593
00:29:30,320 --> 00:29:32,960
I can see you as a truly good guy.

594
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:35,840
I believe in your kind heart.

595
00:29:35,920 --> 00:29:38,880
And I also believe you can be ruthless.

596
00:29:40,760 --> 00:29:42,440
It's time to announce the results.

597
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:44,120
But before we do…

598
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:46,200
- Cindy.
- Yes?

599
00:29:46,280 --> 00:29:48,680
What does today's master class winner get?

600
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:54,680
Today's master class winner
will get a special privilege

601
00:29:54,760 --> 00:29:56,840
for today's campaign.

602
00:29:58,080 --> 00:29:59,400
All right.

603
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:02,360
And now, it's time for the results.

604
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:04,880
Cindy, which contestant…

605
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:09,960
best portrayed
the Heroes vs Villains concept today?

606
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:14,800
The person who did the best today…

607
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:16,400
is…

608
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:22,240
Kimhan.

609
00:30:23,480 --> 00:30:24,680
Okay.

610
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:28,960
It wasn't just good. It left no crumbs.
No cap!

611
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:31,560
I just had to hug my daddy.

612
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:33,240
I was like, "Daddy…"

613
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:36,680
I won!

614
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:38,760
It's nice to win for once.

615
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:42,080
My only regret is that Off isn't here.
That's all I wanted.

616
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:44,400
I really want to see him. Where is he?

617
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:46,320
You have his number? I'll call him.

618
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:50,160
Congratulations to Kimhan.

619
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:53,520
And to Mentor Pancake-Ananda's team.

620
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:56,040
But everyone, please be prepared.

621
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:58,200
Because from now on, it's the real deal.

622
00:31:02,040 --> 00:31:04,440
I'm confident we'll definitely win today.

623
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:07,680
If we don't, you can pinch my arm again.

624
00:31:07,760 --> 00:31:10,960
Don't get too cocky.
You only won your first master class.

625
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:12,520
Don't make me teach you, kid.

626
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:15,160
Bring it on, Kimhan. You're going down.

627
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:59,000
I'm ready for the this episode's campaign.
I'll give it my all.

628
00:31:59,080 --> 00:32:02,040
For this episode,
I'm confident Team Mile will win.

629
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:03,760
We have to win at least one.

630
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:05,080
Hello, everyone.

631
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,280
- Hello.
- Hello.

632
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:09,640
Today, we're at
Kantana Virtual Production Studio.

633
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:12,960
A studio that will take us
to the edge of imagination.

634
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:16,480
We've reached
the fifth campaign of the season.

635
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:18,920
With only three campaigns left,

636
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:22,560
we'll soon know who makes it
to the Final Walk for each team.

637
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:25,240
And who will be the next The Face.

638
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:26,600
For today,

639
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:31,440
you'll shoot a fashion video
under the action hero concept.

640
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:33,360
Let's absolutely kill it today.

641
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:34,880
Let's go!

642
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:36,560
Always at max energy.

643
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:38,400
But my focus is barely 5%.

644
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:41,720
Let's meet the person
giving us today's brief.

645
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:44,040
Bow, Jidanant Tanpithaksidh.

646
00:32:44,120 --> 00:32:48,480
Strategic Marketing Director,
Beauty and Wellbeing,

647
00:32:48,560 --> 00:32:50,400
Unilever Thailand.

648
00:32:50,480 --> 00:32:53,280
Bow, what's the challenge
for the contestants today?

649
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:56,440
Today's challenge
is about more than just looking good.

650
00:32:56,520 --> 00:33:00,360
They also have to show the courage
to protect their loved ones.

651
00:33:00,440 --> 00:33:04,120
Our challenge today
is called "The Guardian Valor."

652
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:07,440
It's an action hero-style fashion video.

653
00:33:07,520 --> 00:33:11,240
The contestants will be set up
in the middle of a city set,

654
00:33:11,320 --> 00:33:13,840
filled with dust, heat, and pollution.

655
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:16,800
For this challenge,
they must hang from a helicopter

656
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:19,040
to rescue our leading lady.

657
00:33:19,120 --> 00:33:21,880
I've never done this before.
I hope Mentor Off has a good plan.

658
00:33:21,960 --> 00:33:25,720
I will execute it as best as I can.

659
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:30,680
Today, to help all the contestants,
Vaseline has prepared the product,

660
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:36,120
Vaseline Gluta-Hya
Photoage Defense SPF50+ PA++++.

661
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:40,760
This youth-hacking sunscreen
will protect everyone's skin

662
00:33:40,840 --> 00:33:43,800
from the heat, dust, and pollution,

663
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:47,080
helping you all overcome
today's tough challenge.

664
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:48,600
Will there be fire effects?

665
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:52,240
Boom, bang, gas releases?

666
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:54,240
As we mentioned, for today,

667
00:33:54,320 --> 00:33:57,920
we have a leading lady
joining your fashion video shoot.

668
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:00,280
So, give a big round of applause

669
00:34:00,360 --> 00:34:02,920
for Palmy from <i>The Face Thailand Season 6</i>!

670
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:08,040
PALMY, THITINAN SUESUMRIT
THE FACE THAILAND SEASON 6

671
00:34:08,120 --> 00:34:09,600
Leo loves her.

672
00:34:09,679 --> 00:34:10,760
<i>Oppa </i>was so ready.

673
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:13,679
He didn't mind the campaign.
He just wanted to carry her.

674
00:34:16,520 --> 00:34:18,320
Palmy is so beautiful.

675
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:20,920
You usually go with others,
but today you're solo.

676
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:22,159
How do you feel?

677
00:34:22,239 --> 00:34:25,719
A bit nervous.
But I feel today will be challenging

678
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:29,199
because I've done the rehearsal,
and it's not easy.

679
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:32,600
But I'm here to help every team
and give it my all.

680
00:34:32,679 --> 00:34:36,080
Thank you so much. The guys
have been smiling since you walked out.

681
00:34:36,159 --> 00:34:38,360
It's quite refreshing for everyone.

682
00:34:38,440 --> 00:34:41,679
All right.
Kimhan, you won the master class.

683
00:34:41,760 --> 00:34:43,199
For today,

684
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:48,120
the master class winner gets
an extra five minutes for the campaign.

685
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,800
Oh, wow!

686
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:51,960
So satisfying today.

687
00:34:52,719 --> 00:34:54,199
It felt like a big advantage.

688
00:34:55,040 --> 00:34:57,600
It was fine. He was not that good.

689
00:34:57,680 --> 00:35:00,360
So he needed more time than the others.

690
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:08,480
But the special perks
for today's campaign don't end there.

691
00:35:08,560 --> 00:35:12,760
We're going to draw lots
to see which tagline each team gets.

692
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:15,320
A representative from each team,
come forward.

693
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:17,360
Choose wisely.

694
00:35:17,440 --> 00:35:18,320
Go ahead and pick.

695
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:21,480
I came first.

696
00:35:21,560 --> 00:35:24,320
When I first walked up,
I wanted the middle one.

697
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:27,400
The camera clearly shows
I touched it first.

698
00:35:27,480 --> 00:35:29,520
When I ask, no one speaks up. See?

699
00:35:29,600 --> 00:35:30,440
Cheater.

700
00:35:30,520 --> 00:35:34,720
Wow, fighting over it like,
"I touched it first!"

701
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:39,400
Come on. We ended up using
the fairest universal method, odd one out.

702
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:41,520
Odd one out!

703
00:35:42,080 --> 00:35:43,080
It's over.

704
00:35:43,160 --> 00:35:45,440
And I still won.
Wow, luck is on my side today.

705
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:47,480
The spirits here were truly powerful.

706
00:35:47,560 --> 00:35:51,200
Okay, open them if you're ready.

707
00:35:55,520 --> 00:35:58,120
For the first team doing this campaign,

708
00:35:58,640 --> 00:36:00,880
it's Mentor Off's team, with the slogan,

709
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:05,120
"You're safe now.
Even through scorching heat or pollution,

710
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:10,000
I'm confident because of Vaseline
Gluta-Hya Photoage Defense SPF50+.

711
00:36:10,080 --> 00:36:13,320
Youth-hacking sunscreen,
protecting skin to look younger."

712
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:14,560
Good luck.

713
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:15,480
Thanks.

714
00:36:16,480 --> 00:36:18,520
It's the hardest tagline.

715
00:36:18,600 --> 00:36:22,920
Like the last campaign,
the hardest outfit won.

716
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:27,120
For our second team,
it will be Mentor Mile's team.

717
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:28,480
You get the slogan,

718
00:36:28,560 --> 00:36:33,040
"Let me protect you with Vaseline
Gluta-Hya Photoage Defense SPF50+.

719
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:36,080
Youth-hacking sunscreen,
protecting skin to look younger."

720
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:38,880
I drew the shortest one.
How do I make it wow?

721
00:36:38,960 --> 00:36:40,720
It's hard. It's very challenging.

722
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:43,920
And for the last team,
it's Team Pancake-Ananda.

723
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,880
With the slogan,

724
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:48,440
"No matter how strong the sun is,
I'm not afraid.

725
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:52,000
Because I have Vaseline
Gluta-Hya Photoage Defense SPF50+.

726
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:56,480
Youth-hacking sunscreen,
protecting our skin to look younger."

727
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:57,600
- Okay.
- Got it.

728
00:36:57,680 --> 00:37:00,120
I got the third tagline.

729
00:37:00,200 --> 00:37:02,520
And we're performing last.

730
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:04,640
Wow, today was just great.

731
00:37:04,720 --> 00:37:07,800
Please welcome the mentors
joining our campaign today.

732
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:10,320
Welcome Mentor Ananda and Mentor Off!

733
00:37:15,120 --> 00:37:18,080
Even though Mile is busy,
he probably has a backup plan.

734
00:37:18,160 --> 00:37:20,640
He wouldn't just leave us hanging.

735
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:23,880
Today, Mentor Mile is busy
and couldn't be here.

736
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:29,440
So, Mentor Mile sent
two talented actors to step in for him.

737
00:37:29,520 --> 00:37:33,480
Give a big round of applause
for Jes and Bible!

738
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:40,760
Wow, they came together.
It's going to be amazing.

739
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:42,400
Hello, I'm Jes Jespipat.

740
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:46,520
I'm stepping in for Mentor Mile.
I'm here with Bible.

741
00:37:46,600 --> 00:37:50,160
We're actors,
so we have quite a bit of experience.

742
00:37:50,240 --> 00:37:52,240
You're messing with my friend a lot, huh?

743
00:37:52,320 --> 00:37:54,280
I didn't mess with anyone. It's him.

744
00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:55,400
- Really?
- Yes.

745
00:37:55,480 --> 00:37:57,920
My mentors today are no joke, Off.

746
00:37:58,000 --> 00:38:00,080
Mentor Jes, Bible. Let me ask something.

747
00:38:00,160 --> 00:38:03,840
Why did Mentor Mile send you two
to take his place?

748
00:38:03,920 --> 00:38:07,800
He's tied up with other duties.
Mentor Mile is quite popular.

749
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:09,720
- Yes, he's hot.
- In high demand.

750
00:38:09,800 --> 00:38:11,680
Are you confident, Mentor Bible?

751
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:13,960
I wouldn't be as confident alone.

752
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:17,000
But I'm here with Jes. He can fight back.

753
00:38:17,080 --> 00:38:18,800
I'm just looking after the boys.

754
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:22,920
I'm not even here to coach them.
I'm here to fight you two.

755
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:24,720
Bible will handle the coaching.

756
00:38:24,800 --> 00:38:26,320
- Right.
- Oh, okay.

757
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:29,720
They have two mentors. Any thoughts,
Mentor Off and Mentor Ananda?

758
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:33,440
Everyone complained it was unfair
for Pancake and Ananda to team up.

759
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:36,280
But look at this.
They bring a helper every episode.

760
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:39,480
They keep sending people.
You're here every episode!

761
00:38:39,560 --> 00:38:42,120
You were here last episode.
You just weren't on set.

762
00:38:42,200 --> 00:38:43,840
I still saw you.

763
00:38:43,920 --> 00:38:45,080
You brought someone!

764
00:38:45,160 --> 00:38:46,320
- Today?
- Did you?

765
00:38:46,400 --> 00:38:49,640
Seeing Jes made me realize
someone could take him on.

766
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:51,800
- Can I call him out here?
- Be my guest.

767
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:54,160
Buddy, come on out and argue with them!

768
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:56,760
Please give a big hand for Tay Tawan!

769
00:38:58,680 --> 00:39:02,400
Tay is already great. Teaming up with Off…

770
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:04,560
The show will definitely be spectacular.

771
00:39:04,640 --> 00:39:06,120
Why are there so many of you?

772
00:39:06,200 --> 00:39:09,520
I'm getting annoyed. I just wanted
to be petty and call someone…

773
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:11,160
To help me out.

774
00:39:11,240 --> 00:39:15,160
As we know, Mentor Off
has won several campaigns.

775
00:39:15,240 --> 00:39:18,720
Will you help him
keep his winning streak today?

776
00:39:18,800 --> 00:39:21,120
I'm not really good at arguing.

777
00:39:21,200 --> 00:39:24,680
I'm here to help my friend.
If we lose, I'll never show my face again.

778
00:39:24,760 --> 00:39:27,560
Wait, what about me? I still have to come.

779
00:39:27,640 --> 00:39:29,320
No, but if they lose, it's on you.

780
00:39:29,400 --> 00:39:31,040
But I think I can take them.

781
00:39:31,120 --> 00:39:32,680
See?

782
00:39:32,760 --> 00:39:34,080
Hello, I'm Tay Tawan.

783
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:36,880
I'm here as someone reasonably well-off.

784
00:39:36,960 --> 00:39:41,320
You can't just come here, make jokes,
and let your team lose.

785
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:43,520
That's unacceptable, Tay Tawan.

786
00:39:43,600 --> 00:39:46,120
We now know the competition order.

787
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:48,480
And the rules for this campaign.

788
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:50,440
Everyone, please go get ready.

789
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:54,480
Do your best, Off.

790
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:58,920
If Off needs help,
I'm more than happy to step in.

791
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:00,160
Give it your all.

792
00:40:00,240 --> 00:40:03,040
Your time starts with the first question.

793
00:40:04,160 --> 00:40:05,760
Wait here for a bit, please.

794
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:07,440
Let me check out the set.

795
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:09,480
We only have 15 minutes to direct them.

796
00:40:09,560 --> 00:40:12,200
And divide that by four
is three minutes each,

797
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:14,680
leaving us three minutes to reset.

798
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:18,160
We have to try it,
so the boys will know how too.

799
00:40:18,240 --> 00:40:19,400
- Standing there.
- Yes.

800
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:21,160
Should they mention the product?

801
00:40:21,240 --> 00:40:23,680
I want the product
to be part of their lives.

802
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:26,840
Do the scene however you like.
You can talk or whatever.

803
00:40:26,920 --> 00:40:29,360
You want them to apply
the product first, right?

804
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:33,160
I just want the product featured.
I'll leave the design up to your team.

805
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:37,400
Okay. So we can start with it,
or bring it in later, right?

806
00:40:37,480 --> 00:40:38,560
Yes.

807
00:40:38,640 --> 00:40:41,000
- They can apply it anytime.
- Exactly.

808
00:40:41,080 --> 00:40:42,800
Where should they use it, you think?

809
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:45,880
- The body. Anywhere from the neck down.
- Neck down.

810
00:40:45,960 --> 00:40:48,560
- And I can give full directions
- The time.

811
00:40:48,640 --> 00:40:50,240
to the female model too, right?

812
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:51,720
- Like instructions?
- Yes.

813
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:53,840
- Just not outshine the boys.
- All right.

814
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:55,200
- Time's up.
- Thank you.

815
00:40:55,280 --> 00:40:56,320
It's quite hard.

816
00:40:56,400 --> 00:41:00,080
Climbing and hanging off the ladder
makes it hard to stay still.

817
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:03,160
The client wants something fun
and completely unique.

818
00:41:03,240 --> 00:41:06,320
So we're giving them
four different storylines.

819
00:41:06,400 --> 00:41:08,200
- Hello.
- Hello.

820
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:09,400
- Hello.
- Hello.

821
00:41:09,480 --> 00:41:11,720
Give me a second. Let me try this.

822
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:12,920
Bible.

823
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:16,080
Honestly, I'm more worried
about the visuals and the acting.

824
00:41:16,160 --> 00:41:19,400
So I went up to test it out
and see which poses worked best.

825
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:23,920
That way, we could give the boys
clear directions on what we wanted.

826
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:26,760
Do you want the product to be used on set?

827
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:29,280
I'm not strictly enforcing how you use it.

828
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:30,800
But I do want it featured.

829
00:41:30,880 --> 00:41:33,640
I should at least see the packaging.

830
00:41:33,720 --> 00:41:35,800
- So the lead uses the product.
- Yes.

831
00:41:35,880 --> 00:41:39,560
So he's not afraid of the sun or dust.
Am I getting that right?

832
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:40,560
Yes.

833
00:41:40,640 --> 00:41:42,120
What do you want to highlight?

834
00:41:42,200 --> 00:41:43,880
I want to highlight the SPF.

835
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:44,960
- Okay.
- Protection.

836
00:41:45,040 --> 00:41:46,520
Focus on the sun protection.

837
00:41:46,600 --> 00:41:49,640
Even if it's fashion,
I'll treat it like a regular scene.

838
00:41:49,720 --> 00:41:52,840
Hearing that put me at ease
because it's right up our alley.

839
00:41:52,920 --> 00:41:54,720
I excel at acting.

840
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:56,440
- Hello.
- Hello.

841
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:58,640
- Give me a second, Bow.
- Sure.

842
00:41:58,720 --> 00:42:01,920
It might look easy,
but because the ladder is…

843
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:05,240
There's not much to hold on to,
and the ladder keeps swinging.

844
00:42:05,320 --> 00:42:08,080
Honestly, keeping your balance
is pretty tough.

845
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:10,360
Think of it as a stage play.

846
00:42:10,440 --> 00:42:13,400
You can see everything,
and the acting must be continuous.

847
00:42:13,480 --> 00:42:15,040
It's quite challenging.

848
00:42:15,120 --> 00:42:18,040
What's the highlight of the product?

849
00:42:18,120 --> 00:42:20,840
It's a type of sunscreen.

850
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:24,160
Is there anything special
you want to highlight about it?

851
00:42:24,240 --> 00:42:26,880
The main feature we're focusing on today

852
00:42:26,960 --> 00:42:31,240
is sun protection and fighting off
pollution and smog.

853
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:32,160
- Right?
- Yes.

854
00:42:32,240 --> 00:42:35,720
They'll use this concept.
They have to overcome obstacles

855
00:42:35,800 --> 00:42:37,080
- like pollution.
- Yes.

856
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:38,400
- The effects?
- Then…

857
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:39,760
Yes.

858
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:43,800
As for the message here,
how serious should the dialogue be?

859
00:42:43,880 --> 00:42:46,400
Quite serious, since it's a new product.

860
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:48,960
Okay. Normally, in commercials,

861
00:42:49,040 --> 00:42:52,840
the models don't really show
much personality.

862
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:53,840
But you won't mind

863
00:42:53,920 --> 00:42:56,080
- if they show personality.
- Not at all.

864
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:57,840
And let their true selves shine.

865
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:59,520
- It's up to you.
- Okay.

866
00:42:59,600 --> 00:43:05,120
I think she's open to letting the guys
show their charm and personality.

867
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:08,080
- Come on.
- Let's go.

868
00:43:08,160 --> 00:43:09,840
- Guys.
- Come on.

869
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:14,600
First, we have five minutes
to figure out their characters.

870
00:43:14,680 --> 00:43:17,640
Tay, you coach Mew and Pom.

871
00:43:17,720 --> 00:43:20,600
Okay, Rome and Bonus, come here.

872
00:43:20,680 --> 00:43:24,480
Rome, you'll play a lover.
You'll be helping each other out.

873
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:26,600
Bonus, you're a painter.

874
00:43:26,680 --> 00:43:31,440
Pom will be a typical,
idealized superhero.

875
00:43:31,520 --> 00:43:34,800
I want Mew to be himself
as much as possible.

876
00:43:34,880 --> 00:43:38,320
In the opening scene,
Bonus, you will look around.

877
00:43:38,400 --> 00:43:42,680
You notice the smog and pollution,
so you apply Vaseline.

878
00:43:42,760 --> 00:43:44,120
Then everyone looks at him.

879
00:43:44,200 --> 00:43:46,120
I have to praise Tay and Off.

880
00:43:46,200 --> 00:43:48,760
They're incredibly creative.

881
00:43:48,840 --> 00:43:51,800
They mixed up the characters for everyone.

882
00:43:51,880 --> 00:43:54,720
Mew is paired up with Bonus as lovers.

883
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:57,480
We laughed looking at each other.
How can we be lovers?

884
00:43:57,560 --> 00:43:59,640
No need to actually apply it. Just act.

885
00:44:00,760 --> 00:44:03,120
Stand up. Decide, then Mew, you're up.

886
00:44:03,200 --> 00:44:05,520
- I'll go.
- With determination. And off you go.

887
00:44:06,520 --> 00:44:10,120
It's hard to keep your balance
on the ladder.

888
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:12,200
Even crossing it alone is tough enough.

889
00:44:12,280 --> 00:44:17,360
Having to bring a girl to the other side
makes it even harder.

890
00:44:17,440 --> 00:44:18,720
Mew, say the middle line.

891
00:44:18,800 --> 00:44:21,400
Bonus will do the first and last lines.

892
00:44:21,480 --> 00:44:22,440
- Okay.
- Okay.

893
00:44:22,520 --> 00:44:25,440
I didn't let them
say the tagline at the end.

894
00:44:25,520 --> 00:44:29,880
It's too long. We wouldn't have
enough time in those 15 minutes.

895
00:44:29,960 --> 00:44:31,880
You look up at the sky, pollution.

896
00:44:31,960 --> 00:44:33,080
Then, you scream.

897
00:44:33,160 --> 00:44:35,880
Pom walks in like a superhero.

898
00:44:35,960 --> 00:44:37,800
Push through and stand in the middle.

899
00:44:37,880 --> 00:44:42,200
Like I said before, I've always wanted
to do something like this.

900
00:44:42,280 --> 00:44:44,840
I'm the superhero. I'm strong and capable.

901
00:44:44,920 --> 00:44:46,480
I'm good at everything.

902
00:44:46,560 --> 00:44:49,760
- It's over-the-top and a bit cringey.
- That's it.

903
00:44:49,840 --> 00:44:51,000
That's it.

904
00:44:51,080 --> 00:44:52,560
- Superhero.
- That's it.

905
00:44:52,640 --> 00:44:56,880
I'm not worried about Pom.
He's pretty bold.

906
00:44:56,960 --> 00:45:00,880
He's reliable and can follow the brief.

907
00:45:02,480 --> 00:45:05,520
Darling! Help me!

908
00:45:05,600 --> 00:45:07,840
- Help me!
- Darling!

909
00:45:07,920 --> 00:45:10,480
I'm totally fine with it.
Everyone got a role.

910
00:45:10,560 --> 00:45:13,800
Our team moves forward together.

911
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:15,600
That's why we get along so well.

912
00:45:18,520 --> 00:45:20,920
Twenty minutes isn't a lot of time.

913
00:45:21,000 --> 00:45:24,440
So, we should be as direct as possible.

914
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:25,960
<i>Mission: Impossible</i>.

915
00:45:26,040 --> 00:45:29,680
Have you seen it? Rescuing the woman,
who is Palmy, on the other side.

916
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:32,920
You swing from the ladder to save her
and bring her back.

917
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:36,240
We had to divide the lines,
so we started with the tagline.

918
00:45:36,320 --> 00:45:38,520
My mind was completely blank.

919
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:41,160
- It has to be like this.
- Hundred percent.

920
00:45:41,240 --> 00:45:44,800
Let me protect you with Vaseline
Gluta-Hya Photoage Defense.

921
00:45:44,880 --> 00:45:47,120
Those five minutes were an open audition

922
00:45:47,200 --> 00:45:50,800
to see who gets to climb
and deliver the lines.

923
00:45:50,880 --> 00:45:56,000
Let me protect you with Vaseline
Gluta-Hya Photoage Defense SPF50+.

924
00:45:56,080 --> 00:45:59,240
Youth-hacking sunscreen,
protecting skin to look younger.

925
00:45:59,320 --> 00:46:01,360
Let me protect you

926
00:46:01,440 --> 00:46:06,480
with Vaseline
Gluta-Hya Photoage Defense SPF50+.

927
00:46:06,560 --> 00:46:09,640
I'm picking Manyoo and Leo
to swing the ladder.

928
00:46:09,720 --> 00:46:13,720
Manyoo gives off a more masculine vibe.

929
00:46:13,800 --> 00:46:15,520
Manyoo has one flaw, his name.

930
00:46:15,600 --> 00:46:17,320
I'm a Liverpool fan, that's all.

931
00:46:17,400 --> 00:46:19,600
Five, four, three, two, action!

932
00:46:21,280 --> 00:46:23,440
Look more confident!

933
00:46:24,560 --> 00:46:28,320
I think he's overthinking
what he has to do.

934
00:46:28,400 --> 00:46:29,840
That's why he looked anxious.

935
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:33,000
He didn't sound confident
delivering the tagline.

936
00:46:33,080 --> 00:46:39,280
Let me protect you with Vaseline
Gluta-Hya Photoage Defense SPF50+.

937
00:46:39,360 --> 00:46:40,440
It's so much pressure.

938
00:46:40,520 --> 00:46:42,880
If I mess up,

939
00:46:42,960 --> 00:46:45,120
I'll drag the whole team down.

940
00:46:45,200 --> 00:46:48,840
Let's switch. Same setup,
just swap Leo and Manyoo.

941
00:46:48,920 --> 00:46:53,560
I wanted to pick Leo
because his tagline is in Korean.

942
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:58,360
And when he got up there,
he had great chemistry with the actress.

943
00:46:58,440 --> 00:47:00,480
I want to cue the tagline. Bible.

944
00:47:05,160 --> 00:47:10,080
Let me protect you with Vaseline
Gluta-Hya Photoage Defense SPF50+.

945
00:47:10,160 --> 00:47:13,800
After this rehearsal,
I feel like, okay, let's talk.

946
00:47:13,880 --> 00:47:16,360
Then we'll focus on the team.

947
00:47:16,440 --> 00:47:17,880
And the shot will look good.

948
00:47:17,960 --> 00:47:20,080
And we'll win the campaign.

949
00:47:20,160 --> 00:47:21,360
Okay, let's go.

950
00:47:23,880 --> 00:47:25,960
We actually have a rough idea.

951
00:47:26,040 --> 00:47:27,760
- Just a quick brief.
- Start timer.

952
00:47:27,840 --> 00:47:31,160
Okay, roughly,
we know the product's features, right?

953
00:47:31,240 --> 00:47:33,200
Let's stand up, it's easier.

954
00:47:33,280 --> 00:47:35,440
Okay, see the blocking?

955
00:47:35,520 --> 00:47:37,240
- It starts up here.
- Yes.

956
00:47:37,320 --> 00:47:40,120
This structure is what
I want them to use as a concept.

957
00:47:40,200 --> 00:47:43,240
Then they can add their own personality
to bring it to life.

958
00:47:43,320 --> 00:47:45,040
Make it fun, things like that.

959
00:47:45,120 --> 00:47:48,280
Okay, my idea is a hero look.

960
00:47:48,360 --> 00:47:50,320
- Yes.
- Inspired by Superman.

961
00:47:50,400 --> 00:47:53,400
For the first five minutes,
Ananda let us share ideas.

962
00:47:53,480 --> 00:47:56,600
Then he shared his, and we combined them.

963
00:47:56,680 --> 00:47:58,560
To get the best result.

964
00:47:58,640 --> 00:48:02,280
Don't forget, you have characters
to maintain while working.

965
00:48:02,360 --> 00:48:03,680
I'll call action.

966
00:48:05,200 --> 00:48:06,680
Action!

967
00:48:09,160 --> 00:48:10,240
Let's start over.

968
00:48:11,640 --> 00:48:15,000
For fun, everyone turn this way.
Lincoln, sit here.

969
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:19,320
Kimhan was quieter than usual today.

970
00:48:19,400 --> 00:48:21,640
He looked really tense today.

971
00:48:21,720 --> 00:48:23,360
I'll play Kim first.

972
00:48:23,440 --> 00:48:25,560
Come up here and do your thing.

973
00:48:25,640 --> 00:48:29,680
Like, say hi, point at him.
He's lazy, right?

974
00:48:29,760 --> 00:48:31,080
You're just chilling.

975
00:48:32,200 --> 00:48:33,560
Groove vibe.

976
00:48:33,640 --> 00:48:37,760
So I thought, it's fine.
He might not have figured it out yet.

977
00:48:37,840 --> 00:48:41,560
I could lead first, give them directions.

978
00:48:41,640 --> 00:48:45,160
I was just setting the framework here.

979
00:48:45,240 --> 00:48:47,280
Okay, Ananda spent a lot of time with me.

980
00:48:47,360 --> 00:48:50,280
Because he might want me
to be a role model for the team.

981
00:48:50,360 --> 00:48:54,520
I was nervous because there were
a lot of issues on set.

982
00:48:54,600 --> 00:48:57,680
I didn't know how to move
or swing on the wire.

983
00:48:57,760 --> 00:49:01,080
Like, how did this work?
What was going on?

984
00:49:01,160 --> 00:49:03,160
All I thought was, "Wow, what is this?"

985
00:49:03,240 --> 00:49:05,080
Oh, slide down!

986
00:49:06,080 --> 00:49:07,000
Don't forget.

987
00:49:09,400 --> 00:49:11,680
Yes.

988
00:49:11,760 --> 00:49:14,440
I felt my height was a big issue today.

989
00:49:14,520 --> 00:49:18,240
The grip spacing on the ladder
just didn't feel right.

990
00:49:18,880 --> 00:49:21,600
- You good? Just slide down.
- Go.

991
00:49:21,680 --> 00:49:25,640
I think he started to worry at this point.

992
00:49:25,720 --> 00:49:29,120
When climbing the ladder, like,
balancing was harder than it looked.

993
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:33,880
It made him anxious,
and he started to lose confidence.

994
00:49:33,960 --> 00:49:35,680
Wondering if he could do it.

995
00:49:35,760 --> 00:49:39,000
He's going to jump
and do a strong action here.

996
00:49:40,920 --> 00:49:42,160
Pull it out a bit more.

997
00:49:42,240 --> 00:49:43,920
Okay, let's try.

998
00:49:45,000 --> 00:49:47,080
Oh, then slide down.

999
00:49:47,160 --> 00:49:48,760
At that moment…

1000
00:49:54,680 --> 00:49:57,160
Go for it. Come on.

1001
00:49:58,200 --> 00:49:59,360
Okay, let's go.

1002
00:50:04,360 --> 00:50:06,320
Let's try it. Okay.

1003
00:50:09,400 --> 00:50:11,920
Lincoln's pose was beautiful.
It was really good.

1004
00:50:12,000 --> 00:50:14,680
He didn't think.
He just went with his instinct.

1005
00:50:14,760 --> 00:50:18,800
No one told him.
We didn't plan for him to do that at all.

1006
00:50:18,880 --> 00:50:22,800
He figured it out himself.
It's the instinct of a rescuer,

1007
00:50:22,880 --> 00:50:25,920
which I think is amazing.
I was so excited for him.

1008
00:50:26,000 --> 00:50:27,040
Want to try again?

1009
00:50:27,120 --> 00:50:28,000
- Yes.
- Okay.

1010
00:50:28,080 --> 00:50:30,320
Or should you play the villain version?

1011
00:50:30,400 --> 00:50:31,480
What do you think?

1012
00:50:31,560 --> 00:50:34,400
I think Ananda saw
that we were running out of time.

1013
00:50:34,480 --> 00:50:37,920
It's fine. I don't regret it.
I'm actually glad to play this role.

1014
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:40,760
It let me show everyone what I could do.

1015
00:50:45,560 --> 00:50:48,840
I think it's definitely different.
What we thought and what we did.

1016
00:50:48,920 --> 00:50:52,680
I doubt other teams thought like we did.
See you at the campaign.

1017
00:50:52,760 --> 00:50:53,880
Just wait and see.

1018
00:51:01,360 --> 00:51:03,920
Welcome back
to The Guardian Valor campaign.

1019
00:51:04,000 --> 00:51:07,440
I would like to introduce
our two special guest judges

1020
00:51:07,520 --> 00:51:10,760
who will be judging our campaign today.

1021
00:51:10,840 --> 00:51:11,880
Our first judge.

1022
00:51:11,960 --> 00:51:14,680
Thailand's legendary supermodel, Cindy.

1023
00:51:14,760 --> 00:51:17,960
And our second judge,
Mentor from <i>The Face Thailand Season 6</i>.

1024
00:51:18,040 --> 00:51:19,000
Anntonia.

1025
00:51:21,040 --> 00:51:24,680
This is my first time meeting Cindy.
She's gorgeous in person.

1026
00:51:24,760 --> 00:51:27,280
I'm blushing. There are many men here.

1027
00:51:27,360 --> 00:51:31,240
Anntonia is beautiful. She should be
Miss Universe, not just first runner-up.

1028
00:51:31,320 --> 00:51:34,000
And now, our first team is ready.

1029
00:51:34,080 --> 00:51:36,160
So please welcome Mentor Off's team.

1030
00:51:40,200 --> 00:51:43,120
Hey, the script is long.
Wow, so many details.

1031
00:51:43,200 --> 00:51:45,280
- Let's go! Get on set!
- Get on set.

1032
00:51:45,360 --> 00:51:48,560
I have four guys, four stories,
three minutes each.

1033
00:51:48,640 --> 00:51:51,160
We want them to perform equally well.

1034
00:51:51,240 --> 00:51:53,080
At least they'll gain experience.

1035
00:51:53,160 --> 00:51:54,320
Start the clock.

1036
00:51:54,400 --> 00:51:57,040
Bonus, look here and notice
the dust and smoke.

1037
00:51:57,120 --> 00:51:57,960
Then apply it.

1038
00:51:58,040 --> 00:52:01,080
Going first made everyone stressed out.

1039
00:52:01,160 --> 00:52:02,280
The vibe changed.

1040
00:52:02,960 --> 00:52:05,040
Don't stress about the script. Just relax.

1041
00:52:05,640 --> 00:52:07,560
Slow it down a bit.

1042
00:52:07,640 --> 00:52:10,480
Okay, ready. Action!

1043
00:52:11,200 --> 00:52:12,120
Yes, that's good.

1044
00:52:12,200 --> 00:52:14,400
It started normally.
No one had to overdo it.

1045
00:52:14,480 --> 00:52:16,800
We knew our characters and followed Off.

1046
00:52:16,880 --> 00:52:18,960
Notice the unusual dust and pollution.

1047
00:52:19,040 --> 00:52:20,960
- Oh, so much dust.
- It's hard.

1048
00:52:21,040 --> 00:52:22,600
It's taking quite a while.

1049
00:52:22,680 --> 00:52:25,360
I tried to get Bonus to act slower.

1050
00:52:25,440 --> 00:52:27,760
He's the main character.
He needs to stand out.

1051
00:52:27,840 --> 00:52:31,200
I wanted to open the scene
with him among the painters.

1052
00:52:31,280 --> 00:52:34,320
He was the only one
who noticed the harmful pollution.

1053
00:52:36,040 --> 00:52:37,240
Help me!

1054
00:52:37,320 --> 00:52:39,240
- Calm down, guys.
- I'm over here! Help!

1055
00:52:39,320 --> 00:52:41,560
- I got this.
- Are the mentors in the frame?

1056
00:52:41,640 --> 00:52:43,760
The mentors are in the frame.

1057
00:52:45,880 --> 00:52:47,680
- Go!
- Act more like a hero.

1058
00:52:50,880 --> 00:52:52,040
Are you all right?

1059
00:52:52,840 --> 00:52:53,920
Let me help you.

1060
00:52:54,000 --> 00:52:57,280
- He doesn't give off the rescuer's vibe.
- Yes.

1061
00:52:57,360 --> 00:52:59,120
Once we were there, time was short.

1062
00:52:59,200 --> 00:53:02,280
Everyone only got one take.
Three minutes each wasn't enough.

1063
00:53:02,360 --> 00:53:03,680
Be more serious.

1064
00:53:03,760 --> 00:53:06,520
I get it.
The first take is always stressful.

1065
00:53:06,600 --> 00:53:08,280
A big crowd. I understand.

1066
00:53:08,360 --> 00:53:10,120
- You're safe now.
- Yes.

1067
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:15,440
Even if I must brave the scorching heat
and pollution.

1068
00:53:15,520 --> 00:53:18,360
Bonus did great overall.
The only issue was the tagline.

1069
00:53:18,440 --> 00:53:22,720
I practiced all morning,
but forgot everything during the shoot.

1070
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:25,320
Okay, cut! Next person. Let's go.

1071
00:53:25,920 --> 00:53:28,600
Wait a minute. Did he skip some lines?

1072
00:53:28,680 --> 00:53:29,960
Okay, that works.

1073
00:53:30,040 --> 00:53:31,960
Honestly, I couldn't hear a thing.

1074
00:53:32,040 --> 00:53:35,720
Going first in this kind of campaign
was a huge disadvantage.

1075
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:37,360
It was highly stressful.

1076
00:53:37,440 --> 00:53:38,920
But we had to do our best.

1077
00:53:39,000 --> 00:53:40,640
Pom, act like a superhero.

1078
00:53:40,720 --> 00:53:44,480
Pom was playing the superhero role.
I believe he could pull it off.

1079
00:53:45,720 --> 00:53:47,160
Help me!

1080
00:53:47,240 --> 00:53:49,040
- Hey!
- Save her!

1081
00:53:49,120 --> 00:53:51,080
He's the top contender.

1082
00:53:51,160 --> 00:53:53,360
Letting Pom go first was a good idea.

1083
00:53:53,440 --> 00:53:56,560
Ultimately, the judges will only choose
one winner.

1084
00:53:56,640 --> 00:53:57,720
Here comes the hero.

1085
00:53:58,880 --> 00:54:01,120
We have Pom making a grand entrance.

1086
00:54:04,280 --> 00:54:06,920
- What's going on?
- He's going for a comedic approach.

1087
00:54:08,680 --> 00:54:09,520
Go!

1088
00:54:10,760 --> 00:54:13,320
The longer we waited,
the more eager I was to start.

1089
00:54:13,400 --> 00:54:16,680
I stepped in
to save the woman in distress.

1090
00:54:17,280 --> 00:54:20,040
Pom did everything perfectly.
I mean, flawlessly.

1091
00:54:20,120 --> 00:54:21,000
You're safe now.

1092
00:54:21,080 --> 00:54:23,800
Don't turn your back to the camera.
Don't do that.

1093
00:54:26,360 --> 00:54:28,280
The tagline…

1094
00:54:28,360 --> 00:54:30,360
Even if I must brave…

1095
00:54:31,480 --> 00:54:35,560
He did decently, but he still messed up
the tagline at the end.

1096
00:54:37,640 --> 00:54:39,480
Let's try again. Talk to her first.

1097
00:54:39,560 --> 00:54:40,840
You're safe now.

1098
00:54:41,600 --> 00:54:44,760
Even if I must brave pollution
and the scorching heat…

1099
00:54:46,600 --> 00:54:49,080
Oh, he completely forgot the line.

1100
00:54:50,080 --> 00:54:51,040
He's just nervous.

1101
00:54:51,120 --> 00:54:53,040
"The scorching heat and pollution."

1102
00:54:54,240 --> 00:54:57,240
I was just in my own head,
trying to remember my lines.

1103
00:54:58,400 --> 00:54:59,640
Just breathe.

1104
00:54:59,720 --> 00:55:03,080
I don't know how to handle them
forgetting their lines. It's tough.

1105
00:55:03,160 --> 00:55:06,080
I think every actor has experienced this
at some point.

1106
00:55:06,160 --> 00:55:08,400
Telling them to calm down doesn't help.

1107
00:55:08,480 --> 00:55:09,480
Go get the script.

1108
00:55:09,560 --> 00:55:11,600
Mentor, step in and help.

1109
00:55:11,680 --> 00:55:14,480
Memorize the tagline
and say it with confidence.

1110
00:55:14,560 --> 00:55:16,480
- We're allowed another take?
- Yes.

1111
00:55:16,560 --> 00:55:18,760
I'm just checking if we can do that?

1112
00:55:18,840 --> 00:55:20,360
One, two, three, action!

1113
00:55:20,440 --> 00:55:24,720
Even if I must brave the scorching heat,
and… or pollution…

1114
00:55:24,800 --> 00:55:26,400
He looked way too stressed.

1115
00:55:26,480 --> 00:55:28,760
As an actor, being in that situation…

1116
00:55:28,840 --> 00:55:30,720
It really sticks with you.

1117
00:55:30,800 --> 00:55:34,440
You want to do your absolute best,
but your mind just goes blank.

1118
00:55:34,520 --> 00:55:35,800
Try again. Say it again.

1119
00:55:35,880 --> 00:55:38,160
Even if I must brave the scorching heat…

1120
00:55:38,240 --> 00:55:40,040
- "Confident…"
- I'm still confident…

1121
00:55:40,120 --> 00:55:41,040
"Because I have…"

1122
00:55:41,120 --> 00:55:44,480
Because I have Vaseline Gluta-Hya.

1123
00:55:44,560 --> 00:55:47,120
Once the tagline fell apart…

1124
00:55:47,200 --> 00:55:49,480
it was impossible to regain focus.

1125
00:55:49,560 --> 00:55:51,960
Even if we prompted him,
he wouldn't register it.

1126
00:55:52,040 --> 00:55:53,280
We're out of time. Next!

1127
00:55:53,360 --> 00:55:55,680
- I hate this. I experienced it before.
- Me too.

1128
00:55:55,760 --> 00:55:56,760
- Been there.
- Yes.

1129
00:55:56,840 --> 00:55:58,200
My mind just went blank.

1130
00:55:58,280 --> 00:56:00,240
Seeing both Bonus and Pom…

1131
00:56:00,320 --> 00:56:04,840
I felt the time was too tight
to only give everyone one take.

1132
00:56:04,920 --> 00:56:07,080
But blanking out and forgetting lines…

1133
00:56:07,160 --> 00:56:08,600
is actually contagious.

1134
00:56:08,680 --> 00:56:11,600
Once it started, it spread to the others.

1135
00:56:11,680 --> 00:56:13,000
You're safe now.

1136
00:56:14,040 --> 00:56:17,120
I remember Mew breathing so heavily.
He was trying to reset.

1137
00:56:19,720 --> 00:56:20,880
What the hell?

1138
00:56:20,960 --> 00:56:22,560
And reset.

1139
00:56:22,640 --> 00:56:23,680
You're safe now.

1140
00:56:23,760 --> 00:56:26,800
Even if we must brave
the scorching heat and pollution,

1141
00:56:26,880 --> 00:56:29,000
we remain confident

1142
00:56:29,080 --> 00:56:32,080
because we have Vaseline Gluta-Hya.

1143
00:56:34,800 --> 00:56:36,320
- "Photoage."
- One more time.

1144
00:56:38,840 --> 00:56:40,960
Oh, man.

1145
00:56:41,040 --> 00:56:44,120
What a bummer. I was so frustrated.

1146
00:56:44,200 --> 00:56:46,640
Again. Take a deep breath and start over.

1147
00:56:46,720 --> 00:56:49,560
It was bad.
The team's morale was terrible.

1148
00:56:49,640 --> 00:56:51,600
- Can I start over?
- Sure.

1149
00:56:51,680 --> 00:56:55,200
Time was running out.
I felt I didn't have a usable take yet.

1150
00:56:55,280 --> 00:56:56,840
So I asked to do all the talking.

1151
00:56:56,920 --> 00:56:58,720
You're safe now.

1152
00:56:58,800 --> 00:57:03,280
Vaseline Gluta-Hya
Photoage Defense SPF50+.

1153
00:57:03,360 --> 00:57:05,960
The sunscreen that hacks youthful skin,
protecting…

1154
00:57:06,560 --> 00:57:10,160
The sunscreen that hacks youthful skin,
protecting it for a younger look.

1155
00:57:10,240 --> 00:57:11,440
- Almost had it.
- Yes.

1156
00:57:12,280 --> 00:57:14,120
I got the hardest lines.

1157
00:57:14,200 --> 00:57:17,320
We did our best. Period.

1158
00:57:17,400 --> 00:57:19,640
Four minutes and twenty seconds left.

1159
00:57:19,720 --> 00:57:21,000
Next, scene four.

1160
00:57:21,080 --> 00:57:22,680
Scene four. What?

1161
00:57:23,600 --> 00:57:26,840
I felt the task was too hard for the boys.

1162
00:57:26,920 --> 00:57:28,400
They had to remember both…

1163
00:57:28,480 --> 00:57:31,000
- Acting and blocking?
- For the others too, yes.

1164
00:57:31,080 --> 00:57:33,680
Only getting one take each
made it really hard.

1165
00:57:33,760 --> 00:57:38,360
If I could go back, I would just do
two scenes and give them two takes each.

1166
00:57:38,440 --> 00:57:40,080
Rome, whenever you're ready.

1167
00:57:44,160 --> 00:57:45,200
- Help!
- Quiet!

1168
00:57:45,280 --> 00:57:48,880
I pushed myself.
Since the others couldn't, it was up to me

1169
00:57:48,960 --> 00:57:50,920
to keep our team in the game.

1170
00:57:51,000 --> 00:57:52,000
- Hold on.
- Babe!

1171
00:57:52,080 --> 00:57:52,960
- Help!
- Quiet!

1172
00:57:53,040 --> 00:57:56,040
Rome was playing Palmy's boyfriend.
He was looking for her.

1173
00:57:56,640 --> 00:57:58,760
- You go first.
- He looks like a hero.

1174
00:57:58,840 --> 00:58:00,200
So strong.

1175
00:58:00,280 --> 00:58:03,800
One punch, two punches,
and pulling Palmy up.

1176
00:58:03,880 --> 00:58:07,280
Rescue her, but she's too scared.
She lacks confidence.

1177
00:58:07,360 --> 00:58:08,280
Are you okay?

1178
00:58:08,360 --> 00:58:11,400
Palmy wasn't confident
about escaping with him.

1179
00:58:11,480 --> 00:58:13,000
Here, apply this first.

1180
00:58:13,720 --> 00:58:15,920
She has to apply sunscreen first.

1181
00:58:16,000 --> 00:58:18,160
Okay, the storyline is solid.

1182
00:58:18,240 --> 00:58:19,880
Okay, it's creative.

1183
00:58:19,960 --> 00:58:22,520
The way they look at each other
is so romantic.

1184
00:58:22,600 --> 00:58:26,240
Rome's part was beautiful.
It was perfect when she came back.

1185
00:58:26,320 --> 00:58:29,320
The way her dress draped down
was so beautiful.

1186
00:58:29,400 --> 00:58:31,160
This is a new side of Rome.

1187
00:58:31,240 --> 00:58:32,720
One hug and say the tagline.

1188
00:58:32,800 --> 00:58:34,160
That's okay.

1189
00:58:34,240 --> 00:58:35,760
You're safe now.

1190
00:58:35,840 --> 00:58:40,360
Even if I must brave the scorching heat
and pollution.

1191
00:58:40,440 --> 00:58:43,120
I remain confident because of…

1192
00:58:43,800 --> 00:58:49,360
Vaseline Gluta-Hya
Photoage Defense SPF50+.

1193
00:58:49,440 --> 00:58:52,720
The sunscreen that hacks youthful skin,

1194
00:58:52,800 --> 00:58:55,720
protecting it for a younger look.

1195
00:58:55,800 --> 00:58:57,600
- That's it.
- Okay.

1196
00:58:57,680 --> 00:58:58,760
Great focus.

1197
00:58:58,840 --> 00:59:03,000
I tried my best to get us through it.

1198
00:59:03,080 --> 00:59:05,680
I want you to say the tagline
one more time, articulate.

1199
00:59:05,760 --> 00:59:08,640
We couldn't fix anything else,
just the tagline.

1200
00:59:08,720 --> 00:59:10,480
He's the only one who pulled it off.

1201
00:59:10,560 --> 00:59:13,200
All right, go for it. You can do this.

1202
00:59:13,280 --> 00:59:14,560
Fifty seconds left.

1203
00:59:14,640 --> 00:59:17,280
Vaseline Gluta-Hya Photoage…

1204
00:59:17,360 --> 00:59:20,560
I hope my take will be good enough
to beat the other teams.

1205
00:59:23,600 --> 00:59:29,120
Rome nailed every mark.
He was our only hope of winning.

1206
00:59:29,200 --> 00:59:30,480
Ten seconds.

1207
00:59:30,560 --> 00:59:35,160
I remain confident because of
Vaseline Gluta-Hya Photoage…

1208
00:59:35,240 --> 00:59:36,080
Skin…

1209
00:59:36,840 --> 00:59:37,960
Sorry.

1210
00:59:38,640 --> 00:59:40,000
Time's up!

1211
00:59:41,560 --> 00:59:43,000
- Use this.
- Did he just say…

1212
00:59:43,080 --> 00:59:46,360
Oh, wow. "Vaseline… pfft." Oh, no.

1213
00:59:46,440 --> 00:59:49,080
Any sound would be better than "pfft."

1214
00:59:49,160 --> 00:59:51,000
It wasn't directed at the client.

1215
00:59:51,520 --> 00:59:52,400
I'm sorry.

1216
00:59:52,480 --> 00:59:54,360
Next up is our second team.

1217
00:59:54,440 --> 00:59:56,160
Please welcome Mentor Mile's team.

1218
00:59:58,240 --> 01:00:00,480
For this campaign,
our team only has one prompt.

1219
01:00:00,560 --> 01:00:02,400
Everyone plays the same role.

1220
01:00:02,480 --> 01:00:05,560
Whenever you're ready.
You have 15 minutes.

1221
01:00:05,640 --> 01:00:06,680
Your time starts now.

1222
01:00:06,760 --> 01:00:11,160
We watched and took note
of their mistakes and strengths.

1223
01:00:11,240 --> 01:00:13,240
We'll apply those lessons to our team.

1224
01:00:18,120 --> 01:00:19,720
- Go!
- Hurry!

1225
01:00:19,800 --> 01:00:22,520
I felt we should give them
minimal information.

1226
01:00:22,600 --> 01:00:26,040
I try to be the kind of director
I would like to work with.

1227
01:00:30,320 --> 01:00:32,000
Leo was playing with his shirt

1228
01:00:32,080 --> 01:00:34,680
to fit the concept they both gave us.

1229
01:00:36,760 --> 01:00:39,600
The moment I touched the ladder,
I felt it wasn't working.

1230
01:00:39,680 --> 01:00:45,480
I couldn't pose.
I knew something was definitely wrong.

1231
01:00:49,680 --> 01:00:53,480
Just like in rehearsal,
we cheered him on from the back.

1232
01:00:55,160 --> 01:00:56,280
How are you?

1233
01:00:56,360 --> 01:00:57,720
Apply the sunscreen on her.

1234
01:00:57,800 --> 01:00:59,680
Let me protect you.

1235
01:01:00,400 --> 01:01:04,640
Leo looks so handsome.
He clearly stands out.

1236
01:01:04,720 --> 01:01:06,200
It's perfect.

1237
01:01:08,960 --> 01:01:10,320
Guys, help!

1238
01:01:10,400 --> 01:01:13,680
I look at the big picture,
the overall mood and feel.

1239
01:01:14,280 --> 01:01:16,040
I focus on the details.

1240
01:01:16,120 --> 01:01:17,360
Leo.

1241
01:01:18,480 --> 01:01:20,080
Peem.

1242
01:01:21,360 --> 01:01:23,800
Vaseline Gluta-Hya Photoage…

1243
01:01:27,280 --> 01:01:30,400
The tagline was in Korean
in your favor, man.

1244
01:01:30,480 --> 01:01:32,080
Is that it? Really?

1245
01:01:32,160 --> 01:01:35,120
This team's advantage
was their short tagline.

1246
01:01:35,200 --> 01:01:38,040
Why does the script look shorter
than the Thai one?

1247
01:01:38,120 --> 01:01:41,680
He forgot the tagline in the first take,
and the blocking was wrong too.

1248
01:01:41,760 --> 01:01:45,320
Because he was actually supposed
to use Vaseline to revive her.

1249
01:01:46,600 --> 01:01:49,120
For take two,
the mentors wanted a new approach,

1250
01:01:49,200 --> 01:01:50,960
which is applying the sunscreen.

1251
01:01:53,720 --> 01:01:57,120
Being the second team,
they saw the flaws from the first round.

1252
01:01:58,600 --> 01:02:01,800
They had time to figure out
how to fix those flaws.

1253
01:02:01,880 --> 01:02:03,280
Leo.

1254
