01:14:32,600 --> 01:14:34,360
Last take.

1500
01:14:34,440 --> 01:14:35,840
Robber, enter.

1501
01:14:35,920 --> 01:14:37,360
Good.

1502
01:14:37,440 --> 01:14:38,640
Donut is doing well.

1503
01:14:38,720 --> 01:14:42,000
I keep my eyes on Donut
because I like his acting.

1504
01:14:42,080 --> 01:14:45,240
- Is he always playing the bad guy?
- Yes, it suits him best.

1505
01:14:45,320 --> 01:14:48,720
Poor Donut.
He didn't get to swing on the ladder.

1506
01:14:48,800 --> 01:14:49,800
Ananda dropped it.

1507
01:14:51,880 --> 01:14:52,800
I'm screwed.

1508
01:14:55,960 --> 01:14:57,280
I'm screwed!

1509
01:15:00,280 --> 01:15:01,600
Keep going. Don't stop.

1510
01:15:02,280 --> 01:15:03,640
Throw it back up.

1511
01:15:04,280 --> 01:15:05,760
Kick him down too. Kick him.

1512
01:15:05,840 --> 01:15:07,000
Turn around and kick.

1513
01:15:07,080 --> 01:15:08,240
Let's just keep going.

1514
01:15:10,240 --> 01:15:11,440
Bye, Donut.

1515
01:15:11,520 --> 01:15:12,920
We're running out of time.

1516
01:15:13,000 --> 01:15:15,200
Oh, she fell down.

1517
01:15:16,680 --> 01:15:19,400
Go. Hold the center for a bit.

1518
01:15:19,480 --> 01:15:20,920
I was barely hanging on.

1519
01:15:21,000 --> 01:15:22,240
If I went to help her…

1520
01:15:22,960 --> 01:15:24,360
I couldn't hold on either.

1521
01:15:24,440 --> 01:15:25,600
Hurry!

1522
01:15:34,760 --> 01:15:37,840
My leading man is dead.

1523
01:15:37,920 --> 01:15:40,400
- My leading man is dead.
- What?

1524
01:15:40,480 --> 01:15:42,240
That shot was when I…

1525
01:15:42,320 --> 01:15:45,440
My hands were slipping
because they were getting wet.

1526
01:15:46,040 --> 01:15:47,280
Just leave me here.

1527
01:15:47,360 --> 01:15:48,720
Thirty seconds left.

1528
01:15:48,800 --> 01:15:51,320
Go. Run up and say your lines.

1529
01:15:51,400 --> 01:15:53,360
Lincoln, sit down. Sit.

1530
01:15:53,440 --> 01:15:56,960
He was rushing. I was afraid
he would ruin his take.

1531
01:15:57,040 --> 01:15:58,640
So I tried to slow him down.

1532
01:15:58,720 --> 01:16:00,040
Okay, focus.

1533
01:16:00,120 --> 01:16:01,200
Show them.

1534
01:16:01,280 --> 01:16:02,200
Say it.

1535
01:16:02,280 --> 01:16:04,640
No matter how intense the sun is,
I'm not afraid.

1536
01:16:04,720 --> 01:16:07,320
I have Vaseline Gluta-Hya Photoage.

1537
01:16:07,400 --> 01:16:12,000
It protects our skin
and keeps us looking young.

1538
01:16:12,080 --> 01:16:14,560
Holy crap, he actually said it.

1539
01:16:14,640 --> 01:16:17,040
And he delivered it perfectly on time.

1540
01:16:17,120 --> 01:16:18,760
Time's up!

1541
01:16:22,080 --> 01:16:23,440
That take was the best.

1542
01:16:23,520 --> 01:16:26,560
Ten, nine, eight…
It felt like a movie script.

1543
01:16:27,200 --> 01:16:28,960
Hey, what's wrong?

1544
01:16:29,040 --> 01:16:31,320
- Hey, is Donut okay?
- Is Donut all right?

1545
01:16:31,400 --> 01:16:32,760
He got kicked.

1546
01:16:32,840 --> 01:16:34,360
Sorry! I kicked Donut's balls.

1547
01:16:34,440 --> 01:16:39,000
It was an accident.
My knee hit his mini donut.

1548
01:16:39,880 --> 01:16:41,240
Oh, right in the balls.

1549
01:16:42,240 --> 01:16:43,080
Keep going.

1550
01:16:43,160 --> 01:16:45,960
At that moment,
I just wanted him to keep going.

1551
01:16:46,040 --> 01:16:48,200
I wanted the team to flow.
I wanted us to win.

1552
01:16:48,280 --> 01:16:49,720
It didn't matter if I got hurt.

1553
01:16:50,360 --> 01:16:54,760
He got kneed right in the middle
of his performance.

1554
01:16:54,840 --> 01:16:56,040
He's so tough.

1555
01:16:56,880 --> 01:16:59,400
They're giving him first aid now.

1556
01:16:59,480 --> 01:17:00,680
Great spirit.

1557
01:17:00,760 --> 01:17:04,400
Donut is the MVP today. He's the MVP.

1558
01:17:07,840 --> 01:17:10,840
You were very brave. Thank you.

1559
01:17:10,920 --> 01:17:13,640
Well done. You did a great job today.

1560
01:17:13,720 --> 01:17:14,840
Win or lose,

1561
01:17:14,920 --> 01:17:17,960
you've already won in my eyes.

1562
01:17:19,880 --> 01:17:23,000
Let's hear some comments from our judges.

1563
01:17:23,080 --> 01:17:25,560
Bow, how did Mentor Off's team do today?

1564
01:17:25,640 --> 01:17:29,120
Honestly, the team was a bit clunky.

1565
01:17:29,200 --> 01:17:31,840
Everyone was given different roles.

1566
01:17:31,920 --> 01:17:35,240
They couldn't reach
their full potential with just one take.

1567
01:17:35,320 --> 01:17:37,640
Pom, for instance, had great posture.

1568
01:17:37,720 --> 01:17:42,000
But when delivering
the tagline at the end, he fell short.

1569
01:17:42,080 --> 01:17:43,560
On the other hand,

1570
01:17:43,640 --> 01:17:46,200
Rome's acting was good and quite natural.

1571
01:17:46,280 --> 01:17:48,160
This was my logic.

1572
01:17:48,240 --> 01:17:51,240
I planned for everyone
to have an equal part.

1573
01:17:51,320 --> 01:17:56,960
Off's strategy made sense.
But the timing might have been off.

1574
01:17:57,040 --> 01:17:59,640
It was just too much going on.

1575
01:17:59,720 --> 01:18:04,680
There wasn't enough time for anyone
to truly show off their skills.

1576
01:18:04,760 --> 01:18:08,200
With so little time
and so many team members,

1577
01:18:08,840 --> 01:18:14,720
the overall performance
didn't meet our expectations.

1578
01:18:14,800 --> 01:18:18,520
I have to say,
Off did a great job during rehearsals.

1579
01:18:18,600 --> 01:18:22,080
He had so many creative ideas.
But with the time limit,

1580
01:18:22,160 --> 01:18:24,080
Rome was the only one who nailed it.

1581
01:18:24,160 --> 01:18:26,360
The second team is Mentor Mile's team,

1582
01:18:26,440 --> 01:18:29,480
led by Mentor Bible and Mentor Jes.

1583
01:18:29,560 --> 01:18:31,240
Bow, how was this team?

1584
01:18:31,320 --> 01:18:34,800
This team knew exactly
where to position themselves in the frame.

1585
01:18:34,880 --> 01:18:37,880
Everyone had a clear role.
I have to praise the mentors.

1586
01:18:37,960 --> 01:18:40,600
The first standout was Manyoo.

1587
01:18:40,680 --> 01:18:43,520
And the other one
I would like to talk about is Leo.

1588
01:18:43,600 --> 01:18:45,160
He looked quite like a model.

1589
01:18:45,240 --> 01:18:50,280
