we wanted an action-romance vibe.

1590
01:18:50,360 --> 01:18:54,360
It's a pity. I'm not sure why Manyoo
didn't get another take.

1591
01:18:54,440 --> 01:18:58,560
Because during rehearsals,
Manyoo didn't do this well.

1592
01:18:58,640 --> 01:19:00,680
I feel bad for Manyoo too.

1593
01:19:00,760 --> 01:19:03,800
He might not have done as well
in rehearsals.

1594
01:19:03,880 --> 01:19:08,920
But I think as mentors, we need to adapt.

1595
01:19:09,000 --> 01:19:12,320
I think one more take for Manyoo
would've been perfect.

1596
01:19:12,400 --> 01:19:16,520
Because Leo got to do it three times.

1597
01:19:16,600 --> 01:19:18,960
I don't think he needed another go.

1598
01:19:19,040 --> 01:19:24,720
I feel like I followed instructions
and gave it my best shot.

1599
01:19:24,800 --> 01:19:27,680
But Peem couldn't really remember it.

1600
01:19:27,760 --> 01:19:30,160
- Compared to the other two.
- Right.

1601
01:19:30,240 --> 01:19:32,680
That's two teams down.
Now for the final team.

1602
01:19:33,280 --> 01:19:35,720
Mentor Ananda's team.

1603
01:19:35,800 --> 01:19:36,960
What surprised me

1604
01:19:37,040 --> 01:19:39,840
is that they interpreted it
like a stage play.

1605
01:19:39,920 --> 01:19:43,120
Everyone had a clear role to play.

1606
01:19:43,200 --> 01:19:47,560
Kimhan's character was very clear.
He controlled his movements well.

1607
01:19:47,640 --> 01:19:52,480
This team had several advantages.
They were smart to keep it as one story.

1608
01:19:52,560 --> 01:19:56,240
You could feel their great teamwork
and good direction.

1609
01:19:56,320 --> 01:19:59,560
Their individual foundations felt natural.

1610
01:19:59,640 --> 01:20:04,680
Out of everyone,
Lincoln had the best chemistry with Palmy.

1611
01:20:04,760 --> 01:20:09,960
Kimhan is naturally
very entertaining to watch.

1612
01:20:10,040 --> 01:20:13,520
When Kimhan was talking,

1613
01:20:13,600 --> 01:20:17,360
Lincoln walked behind him twice.

1614
01:20:23,600 --> 01:20:25,600
When Lincoln was talking, Kimhan stood

1615
01:20:25,680 --> 01:20:26,800
like this.

1616
01:20:27,720 --> 01:20:29,360
Just let him finish the tagline!

1617
01:20:30,280 --> 01:20:33,120
I felt the most relaxed
working with the final team.

1618
01:20:33,200 --> 01:20:36,920
Ananda already had a clear vision
of what he wanted.

1619
01:20:37,000 --> 01:20:40,200
He let the boys act naturally.

1620
01:20:40,280 --> 01:20:42,160
So they could give it their all.

1621
01:20:42,240 --> 01:20:46,240
I really want to praise Donut
for his effort.

1622
01:20:46,320 --> 01:20:47,480
He was an excellent villain.

1623
01:20:49,320 --> 01:20:51,680
He's the hero of the day.

1624
01:20:51,760 --> 01:20:54,520
The show must go on. You're amazing.

1625
01:20:54,600 --> 01:20:56,320
For today's special treat…

1626
01:20:56,400 --> 01:21:01,000
We have a prize for the one person
who performed best.

1627
01:21:01,080 --> 01:21:04,920
The best performer in the campaign
gets a special prize.

1628
01:21:05,000 --> 01:21:08,480
They'll get to be a presenter for Vaseline

1629
01:21:08,560 --> 01:21:10,960
