1630
01:21:11,040 --> 01:21:13,720
- Oh, wow.
- Yes.

1631
01:21:13,800 --> 01:21:17,880
And now it's time to find out
the results of today's campaign.

1632
01:21:17,960 --> 01:21:20,840
Bow, which team

1633
01:21:20,920 --> 01:21:24,880
performed best
in The Guardian Valor campaign?

1634
01:21:25,640 --> 01:21:28,000
And the winning team is…

1635
01:21:37,480 --> 01:21:40,560
Kimhan from Team Pancake-Ananda.

1636
01:21:42,120 --> 01:21:47,040
Congratulations to Kimhan
from Team Pancake-Ananda.

1637
01:21:47,120 --> 01:21:50,200
I wonder if it's really as good
as the client says.

1638
01:21:50,280 --> 01:21:52,640
Lincoln kept walking back and forth.

1639
01:21:52,720 --> 01:21:54,760
I'll wait and see
how the final edit looks.

1640
01:22:17,680 --> 01:22:19,200
Help me!

1641
01:22:32,040 --> 01:22:33,520
Are you okay?

1642
01:22:44,240 --> 01:22:46,960
No matter how intense the sun is,
I'm not afraid.

1643
01:22:47,040 --> 01:22:50,240
Because I have Vaseline
Gluta-Hya Photoage Defense SPF50+.

1644
01:22:50,320 --> 01:22:53,680
The sunscreen that hacks youthful skin.
It protects your skin

1645
01:22:53,760 --> 01:22:56,880
and keeps us looking young.

1646
01:22:56,960 --> 01:22:58,640
How is it?

1647
01:22:58,720 --> 01:23:00,840
So this is what victory smells like.

1648
01:23:00,920 --> 01:23:02,560
Remember this.

1649
01:23:02,640 --> 01:23:03,600
It's so satisfying.

1650
01:23:04,440 --> 01:23:06,440
It still went according to plan.

1651
01:23:06,520 --> 01:23:07,640
It still worked out.

1652
01:23:07,720 --> 01:23:10,000
For today, I would like to thank Bow…

1653
01:23:10,080 --> 01:23:11,280
Thank you, Cindy.

1654
01:23:11,360 --> 01:23:14,640
And thank you, Anntonia,
for judging our campaign today.

1655
01:23:14,720 --> 01:23:16,080
Thank you so much.

1656
01:23:16,840 --> 01:23:20,480
Also, please give a big round of applause
to our leading lady…

1657
01:23:20,560 --> 01:23:23,160
Palmy from <i>The Face Thailand Season 6</i>.

1658
01:23:24,040 --> 01:23:27,480
I feel like I've experienced it all today.
Accidents, tough briefs.

1659
01:23:27,560 --> 01:23:30,320
My team had everything,
but it might have been too much.

1660
01:23:30,400 --> 01:23:31,720
I have to accept it.

1661
01:23:31,800 --> 01:23:34,200
We've won for weeks,
it's okay to lose sometimes.

1662
01:23:34,280 --> 01:23:36,680
Wow, suddenly so humble
when his team loses.

1663
01:23:36,760 --> 01:23:38,440
Instantly becomes the good guy.

1664
01:24:24,400 --> 01:24:25,720
Hello.

1665
01:24:25,800 --> 01:24:28,200
- Hello.
- Hello.

1666
01:24:28,800 --> 01:24:33,080
When she first came in, we just talked.
Because she wasn't there that day.

1667
01:24:33,160 --> 01:24:34,680
Tell me how it went that day.

1668
01:24:34,760 --> 01:24:37,360
I had an image in my head
of how it should be.

1669
01:24:37,440 --> 01:24:39,680
But this is how we are.

1670
01:24:39,760 --> 01:24:41,160
So we just did it our way.

1671
01:24:41,240 --> 01:24:43,800
And you followed Ananda's brief.

1672
01:24:43,880 --> 01:24:47,000
Did he guide you,
or did you add your own ideas?

1673
01:24:47,080 --> 01:24:49,920
- We added a lot of our own ideas.
- See?

1674
01:24:50,000 --> 01:24:52,400
It was hard because it was in Thai.

1675
01:24:52,480 --> 01:24:55,120
And there were many words I just learned.

1676
01:24:55,200 --> 01:24:57,400
I think I did pretty well that day.

1677
01:24:57,480 --> 01:24:59,240
- I've never done it before.
- Okay.

1678
01:24:59,320 --> 01:25:01,480
You think you did your best.

1679
01:25:01,560 --> 01:25:03,400
But maybe someone else did better.

1680
01:25:06,160 --> 01:25:07,400
We didn't win.

1681
01:25:07,480 --> 01:25:11,440
Why do I always have to be the one
to choose someone to go in?

1682
01:25:12,120 --> 01:25:13,640
Let's try sending Kimhan in.

1683
01:25:16,560 --> 01:25:18,800
I just want Kimhan to go in and see

1684
01:25:18,880 --> 01:25:21,760
