when you're in there.

1685
01:25:21,840 --> 01:25:23,680
I've said this before.

1686
01:25:23,760 --> 01:25:26,400
You won't die, just go in and fight.

1687
01:25:26,480 --> 01:25:27,520
Understood.

1688
01:25:27,600 --> 01:25:30,640
If I go to the Black Room,
I'll try to speak clearly.

1689
01:25:30,720 --> 01:25:33,040
Fight my hardest, so I won't have regrets.

1690
01:25:33,120 --> 01:25:34,080
I'm ready.

1691
01:25:34,680 --> 01:25:36,720
I can see the hope in your eyes.

1692
01:25:36,800 --> 01:25:38,960
Not many get to experience the Black Room.

1693
01:25:39,040 --> 01:25:41,080
- Love you. Give me a hug.
- Let's hug.

1694
01:25:41,160 --> 01:25:42,920
- See you later.
- See you.

1695
01:25:43,000 --> 01:25:47,000
I don't want Lincoln and Donut
to worry that I'm too upset or anything.

1696
01:25:47,080 --> 01:25:48,480
I want them to stay strong.

1697
01:25:48,560 --> 01:25:49,920
Take care of our team.

1698
01:25:50,000 --> 01:25:51,080
Take care of our team.

1699
01:25:51,160 --> 01:25:52,640
I was obviously sad.

1700
01:25:52,720 --> 01:25:53,920
We were pretty close.

1701
01:25:58,000 --> 01:26:00,040
But it's okay.

1702
01:26:00,120 --> 01:26:04,400
I mean, we will meet and work
together again out there anyway.

1703
01:26:04,480 --> 01:26:06,240
What I mean is…

1704
01:26:06,320 --> 01:26:09,480
Like a university.
We come to learn and gain skills together.

1705
01:26:09,560 --> 01:26:14,360
Thanks for teaching me
those little tricks.

1706
01:26:15,880 --> 01:26:17,040
I'm such a rookie.

1707
01:26:17,120 --> 01:26:18,200
I started from zero.

1708
01:26:18,280 --> 01:26:20,960
You always shared your basics with me,

1709
01:26:21,040 --> 01:26:24,760
which really helped me work better.

1710
01:26:25,520 --> 01:26:27,040
So thank you very much.

1711
01:26:28,600 --> 01:26:29,440
That's all.

1712
01:26:29,520 --> 01:26:32,480
But deep down, I know he'll come back.

1713
01:26:32,560 --> 01:26:35,480
Because his words are very powerful.

1714
01:26:37,760 --> 01:26:39,760
- Yes, Dad.
- Oh, wow.

1715
01:26:39,840 --> 01:26:42,000
You guys might as well
sit on the same side.

1716
01:26:42,680 --> 01:26:43,920
Okay, so you all know.

1717
01:26:44,000 --> 01:26:48,520
But I must admit
I made a mistake with the plan.

1718
01:26:48,600 --> 01:26:50,280
So, as everyone saw,

1719
01:26:50,360 --> 01:26:51,600
the result is we lost.

1720
01:26:52,840 --> 01:26:54,160
I hate losing the most.

1721
01:26:54,240 --> 01:26:58,160
At least we lost with dignity.
I gave everyone a role.

1722
01:26:58,240 --> 01:27:00,200
Maybe I gave you too much to do.

1723
01:27:00,280 --> 01:27:03,360
While other teams
focused on just one thing.

1724
01:27:03,440 --> 01:27:06,000
And another thing
I have to apologize for is…

1725
01:27:06,080 --> 01:27:09,280
I gave you too little room for error.

1726
01:27:09,960 --> 01:27:11,600
First of all,

1727
01:27:11,680 --> 01:27:14,120
I think the boys needed a friend then.

1728
01:27:14,200 --> 01:27:15,760
I'll be that friend for them.

1729
01:27:15,840 --> 01:27:18,440
What were your mistakes?
I want to hear them.

1730
01:27:18,520 --> 01:27:19,840
- Let me go first.
- Sure.

1731
01:27:19,920 --> 01:27:21,560
I think there were a lot.

1732
01:27:21,640 --> 01:27:23,680
And way below my usual standard.

1733
01:27:23,760 --> 01:27:28,120
But I believe
we'll take these past mistakes

1734
01:27:28,200 --> 01:27:31,400
and redeem ourselves in the next round.

1735
01:27:31,480 --> 01:27:34,920
Time was short.
I went first out of everyone, right?

1736
01:27:35,000 --> 01:27:38,600
And I didn't want to take too long,
so the others could go too.

1737
01:27:38,680 --> 01:27:39,800
That was on my mind.

1738
01:27:39,880 --> 01:27:42,080
Critiquing yourself is a good thing.

1739
01:27:42,160 --> 01:27:44,080
It's really practical.

1740
01:27:44,160 --> 01:27:47,280
Fix it today, and be better tomorrow.

1741
01:27:47,360 --> 01:27:49,480
Fix it today, and be better tomorrow.

1742
01:27:49,560 --> 01:27:50,960
So I want everyone

1743
01:27:51,640 --> 01:27:53,680
to acknowledge their own mistakes.

1744
01:27:56,280 --> 01:27:57,880
- Hello.
- Hello.

1745
01:27:57,960 --> 01:28:01,400
When Jes and Bible walked in,
I tried to keep the energy positive.

1746
01:28:01,480 --> 01:28:03,320
Welcoming them with a smile.

1747
01:28:03,400 --> 01:28:04,640
And they smiled back.

1748
01:28:04,720 --> 01:28:07,480
How was the latest week?

1749
01:28:07,560 --> 01:28:09,840
Honestly, that day was…

1750
01:28:09,920 --> 01:28:12,480
Overall, the team didn't do well.

1751
01:28:12,560 --> 01:28:14,880
From my perspective,
I should apologize to Gluf.

1752
01:28:14,960 --> 01:28:17,560
For not giving you a chance
in that campaign.

1753
01:28:17,640 --> 01:28:21,600
The reason was you might be
too young for the storyline.

1754
01:28:21,680 --> 01:28:24,600
I talked to Mile about it.
Mile had thought the same.

1755
01:28:24,680 --> 01:28:26,160
And I feel Mile was right.

1756
01:28:26,240 --> 01:28:28,520
Just keep it in mind for the coming weeks.

1757
01:28:28,600 --> 01:28:32,960
What I want to see improve
is exactly this.

1758
01:28:33,040 --> 01:28:34,560
The emotions you convey.

1759
01:28:34,640 --> 01:28:37,960
Because to me,
that's the most important thing.

1760
01:28:38,040 --> 01:28:40,520
And mainly, try to have fun
with the campaigns.

1761
01:28:40,600 --> 01:28:44,160
It shifts you from being overly pressured
to being open to everything.

1762
01:28:44,240 --> 01:28:45,520
Try new things.

1763
01:28:45,600 --> 01:28:50,360
Don't take it too seriously.
I'm just here to share my experience.

1764
01:28:50,440 --> 01:28:55,120
Mile actually sent a tape too
since he's still in Brazil.

1765
01:28:55,200 --> 01:28:59,640
Everyone, I see your effort.
But let's get straight to the point.

1766
01:28:59,720 --> 01:29:02,760
It's a shame our team lost.

1767
01:29:02,840 --> 01:29:08,240
So I have to send one of you
to the Black Room.

1768
01:29:08,320 --> 01:29:11,480
Man, no matter how well we do,
why is it never enough?

1769
01:29:11,560 --> 01:29:14,920
We might have made tiny mistakes,
and the other team made none.

1770
01:29:15,000 --> 01:29:18,440
I was somewhat prepared
that it would be me.

1771
01:29:19,480 --> 01:29:20,640
Have you practiced?

1772
01:29:20,720 --> 01:29:23,000
No. We just talked.

1773
01:29:23,080 --> 01:29:24,800
But I'm okay. Do your best for me.

1774
01:29:24,880 --> 01:29:26,080
Ready to fight.

1775
01:29:26,160 --> 01:29:29,480
- You won't make any sense in there.
- I might.

1776
01:29:29,560 --> 01:29:32,760
Why did Mentor Pancake
send me to the Black Room?

1777
01:29:33,760 --> 01:29:34,920
What should I say next?

1778
01:29:35,000 --> 01:29:36,440
Okay, got it.

1779
01:29:38,200 --> 01:29:39,920
Let's just practice for this round.

1780
01:29:41,240 --> 01:29:42,680
Because we won!

1781
01:29:45,200 --> 01:29:47,920
It feels like I went into the Black Room
and was reborn.

1782
01:29:48,000 --> 01:29:49,680
Without even setting foot inside.

1783
01:29:49,760 --> 01:29:52,720
I think she taught me very well.

1784
01:29:57,400 --> 01:30:01,240
We won! Did you hear that? We won!

1785
01:30:02,080 --> 01:30:04,200
What is this? Should I be sad or happy?

1786
01:30:04,280 --> 01:30:05,240
Or what exactly?

1787
01:30:08,840 --> 01:30:09,840
What the heck.

1788
01:30:09,920 --> 01:30:13,240
- I'm half sad, half happy.
- Doctor!

1789
01:30:13,320 --> 01:30:15,480
A doctor can't help you right now.

1790
01:30:15,560 --> 01:30:18,360
I need a psychiatrist.

1791
01:30:19,600 --> 01:30:22,360
I'm done playing.
Do this again, call an ambulance.

1792
01:30:22,440 --> 01:30:23,520
Come pick me up.

1793
01:30:23,600 --> 01:30:25,120
The person chosen today

1794
01:30:25,200 --> 01:30:28,640
might not be the worst performer.

1795
01:30:28,720 --> 01:30:32,000
I just want him to go and fight.
He should put up a good fight.

1796
01:30:32,080 --> 01:30:33,120
And fight well.

1797
01:30:33,200 --> 01:30:34,200
Mew.

1798
01:30:35,360 --> 01:30:36,880
- No.
- I ask for just one thing.

1799
01:30:36,960 --> 01:30:40,320
Please be the first Black Room winner
this season.

1800
01:30:40,400 --> 01:30:42,760
Can I go instead of Mew? I'm volunteering.

1801
01:30:42,840 --> 01:30:44,440
Can I take his place?

1802
01:30:44,520 --> 01:30:45,800
Or can I join him?

1803
01:30:45,880 --> 01:30:47,880
He's been stressed for many episodes.

1804
01:30:47,960 --> 01:30:51,280
And I don't want him
to be even more stressed.

1805
01:30:52,280 --> 01:30:53,640
No, this is…

1806
01:30:53,720 --> 01:30:55,520
- I know you love him.
- Yes.

1807
01:30:55,600 --> 01:30:59,120
But he needs to be on his own.
How long will you keep protecting him?

1808
01:30:59,200 --> 01:31:01,720
Can two of us go?
He wanted me to go with him.

1809
01:31:01,800 --> 01:31:04,480
Why would I help her
by sending two of you?

1810
01:31:04,560 --> 01:31:07,600
It's like sending you to another campaign.

1811
01:31:07,680 --> 01:31:09,280
You said the same thing to Fox.

1812
01:31:09,360 --> 01:31:10,640
- To who?
- Fox.

1813
01:31:10,720 --> 01:31:11,920
- Fox?
- No.

1814
01:31:12,000 --> 01:31:15,240
- That hurts.
- I truly believe you can fight.

1815
01:31:15,320 --> 01:31:16,960
But Fox isn't as good as you.

1816
01:31:17,040 --> 01:31:19,280
You'll definitely come back.
I believe that.

1817
01:31:19,360 --> 01:31:22,800
Mew is the best talker here.

1818
01:31:22,880 --> 01:31:27,840
We're past the halfway mark now.
It must be around episode six, right?

1819
01:31:27,920 --> 01:31:31,440
So I need to look ahead to the Final Walk.

1820
01:31:31,520 --> 01:31:34,960
It's a really tough choice,
but I have to choose Gluf.

1821
01:31:35,040 --> 01:31:38,880
Because Gluf won't be able
to participate in the Final Walk.

1822
01:31:38,960 --> 01:31:42,880
It was a very difficult decision to make.

1823
01:31:42,960 --> 01:31:44,200
I completely understand.

1824
01:31:44,280 --> 01:31:48,160
Mile wants to give a chance to those
still eligible for the Final Walk.

1825
01:31:49,040 --> 01:31:51,960
If I were Mile,
I would have made the same choice.

1826
01:31:52,040 --> 01:31:55,360
So this week, it's Gluf.

1827
01:31:55,440 --> 01:31:59,480
The reason is, we can't deny
that we're in a competition.

1828
01:31:59,560 --> 01:32:02,240
But don't think
the Final Walk is everything in life.

1829
01:32:02,320 --> 01:32:04,040
In our entertainment industry,

1830
01:32:04,120 --> 01:32:07,040
I've been around for over ten years
to get to where I am.

1831
01:32:07,120 --> 01:32:08,240
It's incredibly hard.

1832
01:32:08,840 --> 01:32:11,720
Every mistake is a lesson.

1833
01:32:11,800 --> 01:32:14,320
Opportunities are very rare.

1834
01:32:14,400 --> 01:32:20,240
So realize its value,
take that energy, and fight.

1835
01:32:20,840 --> 01:32:22,720
And tell Mentor Pancake your reasons.

1836
01:32:22,800 --> 01:32:26,000
Before you go in,
Mile has another clip for you to watch.

1837
01:32:26,520 --> 01:32:28,160
- It's private.
- Private.

1838
01:32:28,240 --> 01:32:31,760
Deep down, I think all the boys feel bad

1839
01:32:31,840 --> 01:32:33,680
after living together for so long.

1840
01:32:33,760 --> 01:32:36,600
One of their friends has
to go into a room, not knowing

1841
01:32:36,680 --> 01:32:39,200
if they'll come back out or have to leave.

1842
01:32:39,280 --> 01:32:41,480
This is your second time
in the Black Room.

1843
01:32:41,560 --> 01:32:45,520
I'm confident that this time,

1844
01:32:45,600 --> 01:32:51,040
Gluf, you'll communicate
with Mentor Pancake and Ananda very well.

1845
01:32:51,640 --> 01:32:52,800
I'm rooting for you.

1846
01:32:52,880 --> 01:32:54,040
Keep fighting.

1847
01:32:54,120 --> 01:32:57,360
I'll wait to see you
after I go back to Thailand. Okay?

1848
01:32:57,440 --> 01:32:59,240
I think if I hadn't prepared

1849
01:32:59,320 --> 01:33:03,800
and faced this situation unexpectedly,
I would've been much more shocked.

1850
01:33:03,880 --> 01:33:07,520
It would be much harder
to keep my composure.

1851
01:33:43,280 --> 01:33:44,560
Hello.

1852
01:33:48,840 --> 01:33:51,360
Why is it Mew and Gluf today?

1853
01:33:51,440 --> 01:33:52,280
Mew first.

1854
01:33:52,360 --> 01:33:56,760
I'm here today because Mentor Off
chose me from the last campaign.

1855
01:33:56,840 --> 01:34:00,640
I looked at your portfolio.
You did a great job on everything.

1856
01:34:00,720 --> 01:34:03,680
Honestly, at first,
I didn't know if I would make it here.

1857
01:34:03,760 --> 01:34:06,880
I booked a flight to Canada.

1858
01:34:06,960 --> 01:34:10,080
But something told me
to postpone my flight and come.

1859
01:34:10,160 --> 01:34:12,600
Mentor Pancake, you can see
I'm trying to improve.

1860
01:34:12,680 --> 01:34:14,640
From the first episode until now.

1861
01:34:14,720 --> 01:34:17,160
Whatever the mentors
tell me to do, I'll do it.

1862
01:34:17,240 --> 01:34:20,360
If the mentors want me to be feminine,
I'll be feminine.

1863
01:34:20,440 --> 01:34:22,120
I can be manly too.

1864
01:34:22,200 --> 01:34:23,920
You prepared really well.

1865
01:34:24,000 --> 01:34:26,880
What did Mentor Off say
about coming to see me?

1866
01:34:26,960 --> 01:34:31,560
Mentor Off told me
to fight Mentor Pancake.

1867
01:34:31,640 --> 01:34:33,600
And to be confident.

1868
01:34:33,680 --> 01:34:36,160
When I was chosen,
Bonus asked to come instead.

1869
01:34:36,240 --> 01:34:39,520
- But I think I would be better.
- It should have sent both of you.

1870
01:34:39,600 --> 01:34:41,720
I think you would be kind.

1871
01:34:41,800 --> 01:34:45,000
Even though you're wearing red
and wings today.

1872
01:34:45,080 --> 01:34:48,400
You might be a kind devil.

1873
01:34:49,280 --> 01:34:51,440
Or you might both be going back to Canada.

1874
01:34:51,520 --> 01:34:54,440
I think you can make
a better decision than that.

1875
01:34:54,520 --> 01:34:57,480
Will I give you a chance?
Let me think about it.

1876
01:34:57,560 --> 01:34:59,400
There's one thing I want to tell you.

1877
01:34:59,480 --> 01:35:02,560
I understand the show
needs entertainment value.

1878
01:35:02,640 --> 01:35:06,440
But sometimes,
there has to be a limit. A boundary.

1879
01:35:06,520 --> 01:35:08,640
Because I saw in the footage…

1880
01:35:08,720 --> 01:35:13,800
Or backstage, there were moments
where your words weren't very nice.

1881
01:35:13,880 --> 01:35:15,560
Or your expressions at times.

1882
01:35:15,640 --> 01:35:16,840
- You know that?
- Yes.

1883
01:35:16,920 --> 01:35:19,320
Do you know it yourself,
or did someone tell you?

1884
01:35:19,960 --> 01:35:21,440
I realized it myself too.

1885
01:35:21,520 --> 01:35:25,320
Because in my head at the time,
I thought it would make things more fun.

1886
01:35:25,400 --> 01:35:28,120
But I also asked the crew
if we could shoot it again.

1887
01:35:28,200 --> 01:35:30,800
This is what you must be
most careful about.

1888
01:35:30,880 --> 01:35:33,760
In this industry,
sometimes there are no second takes.

1889
01:35:33,840 --> 01:35:36,920
People don't know the real you.
They might not get the joke.

1890
01:35:37,000 --> 01:35:39,240
Sometimes it shows disrespect.

1891
01:35:39,320 --> 01:35:41,520
Both to yourself and to others.

1892
01:35:43,320 --> 01:35:45,000
Why Gluf today?

1893
01:35:45,080 --> 01:35:48,920
I got a message from Mentor Mile.
He recorded a clip.

1894
01:35:49,000 --> 01:35:53,760
Explaining why he chose me
and the reasons behind it.

1895
01:35:53,840 --> 01:35:55,000
Why is that?

1896
01:35:55,080 --> 01:35:58,200
Mentor Mile said he wanted
to increase the team's chances

1897
01:35:58,280 --> 01:36:00,200
of making it to the Final Walk.

1898
01:36:02,160 --> 01:36:04,960
I'm no longer eligible, so he sent me in.

1899
01:36:05,040 --> 01:36:08,560
But in terms of performance,
what did your mentor say?

1900
01:36:09,600 --> 01:36:11,760
You weren't here for the last campaign.

1901
01:36:11,840 --> 01:36:15,080
And he didn't get
to perform with everyone else.

1902
01:36:15,160 --> 01:36:18,560
The mentors let the others act,
and he didn't get to perform.

1903
01:36:18,640 --> 01:36:22,360
But you're the one
the Master Mentor said could act.

1904
01:36:22,440 --> 01:36:24,680
But Mentor Mile
didn't consider this at all.

1905
01:36:24,760 --> 01:36:28,840
Mentor Mile didn't make the decision.
It was Mentor Jes and Mentor Bible.

1906
01:36:29,560 --> 01:36:31,840
Actually, both mentors said

1907
01:36:31,920 --> 01:36:34,480
they felt bad for not giving me
a chance to perform.

1908
01:36:34,560 --> 01:36:37,120
But I understand. Since time was so short…

1909
01:36:37,200 --> 01:36:38,920
Everyone should have the right.

1910
01:36:40,600 --> 01:36:41,720
I was going to save you.

1911
01:36:41,800 --> 01:36:45,560
But it seems your mentors
aren't as invested.

1912
01:36:45,640 --> 01:36:46,720
They are invested.

1913
01:36:46,800 --> 01:36:50,760
If you give me a chance,
I'll leap even higher from where I stand.

1914
01:36:50,840 --> 01:36:54,000
I'll show you that I can do it.

1915
01:36:54,080 --> 01:36:58,160
I'll go talk to the mentors
to see if they want to save you.

1916
01:36:58,240 --> 01:37:00,720
Because I think both of these portfolios…

1917
01:37:00,800 --> 01:37:02,800
have interesting work.

1918
01:37:04,520 --> 01:37:07,080
- You look beautiful.
- Time to spread my wings.

1919
01:37:07,160 --> 01:37:09,440
- Bigger wings than before.
- Absolutely.

1920
01:37:15,120 --> 01:37:17,560
Wow, that outfit.

1921
01:37:17,640 --> 01:37:19,400
Bright red with black wings.

1922
01:37:19,480 --> 01:37:22,240
Mew shouldn't have worn wings
in the last episode.

1923
01:37:22,320 --> 01:37:24,640
She's ready to slaughter. I can tell.

1924
01:37:24,720 --> 01:37:27,040
I talked to Gluf.

1925
01:37:27,120 --> 01:37:29,880
You guys didn't give him a chance
in the campaign, right?

1926
01:37:29,960 --> 01:37:30,800
- Right.
- Yes.

1927
01:37:30,880 --> 01:37:31,720
Why?

1928
01:37:31,800 --> 01:37:36,240
Time was short, and we felt the others
were better suited for this campaign.

1929
01:37:36,320 --> 01:37:39,040
It's not strange
that we didn't give him a chance.

1930
01:37:39,120 --> 01:37:40,840
You don't always play the lead.

1931
01:37:40,920 --> 01:37:42,080
And he was right there.

1932
01:37:42,160 --> 01:37:46,080
I didn't cut him out from the backdrop
or the product billboard.

1933
01:37:46,160 --> 01:37:47,360
Why ask that?

1934
01:37:47,440 --> 01:37:51,280
And on that day,
not everyone got to say the tagline.

1935
01:37:51,360 --> 01:37:53,000
- Not everyone.
- Not everyone.

1936
01:37:53,080 --> 01:37:54,800
Why did Gluf go in?

1937
01:37:54,880 --> 01:37:56,920
The reason? I told him honestly.

1938
01:37:57,000 --> 01:37:59,800
That he has no chance
of making the Final Walk.

1939
01:37:59,880 --> 01:38:01,040
The others still do.

1940
01:38:01,120 --> 01:38:03,760
I don't know how much of a chance,
but they have one.

1941
01:38:03,840 --> 01:38:05,280
I was going to save him.

1942
01:38:05,360 --> 01:38:07,480
But after hearing Jes and Bible speak,

1943
01:38:07,560 --> 01:38:09,960
I feel sorry for him.

1944
01:38:10,040 --> 01:38:11,520
Because even if he returns,

1945
01:38:11,600 --> 01:38:13,560
he won't even know what his role is.

1946
01:38:13,640 --> 01:38:16,320
Jes and Bible, it's their first time here.

1947
01:38:16,400 --> 01:38:19,480
They're getting hit with a heavy impact.

1948
01:38:19,560 --> 01:38:20,880
As for Mew.

1949
01:38:20,960 --> 01:38:22,520
- Yes.
- Why him?

1950
01:38:22,600 --> 01:38:25,120
Mew's test scores
were great in every aspect.

1951
01:38:25,200 --> 01:38:28,720
But we also grade based on his behavior.

1952
01:38:28,800 --> 01:38:30,000
For example, he said,

1953
01:38:30,080 --> 01:38:33,960
"Mentor Off already has his favorites."
Telling others that isn't a good thing.

1954
01:38:34,040 --> 01:38:37,280
I don't like that.
I want him to change his mindset.

1955
01:38:37,360 --> 01:38:40,040
Being good at what you do
means you should be a good person.

1956
01:38:40,120 --> 01:38:42,160
The show doesn't need someone who is rude.

1957
01:38:42,240 --> 01:38:45,920
You have to talk to him
because I think it's very important.

1958
01:38:46,000 --> 01:38:47,720
I see that point too.

1959
01:38:47,800 --> 01:38:52,800
Mew is sweet.
He just chose the wrong words.

1960
01:38:52,880 --> 01:38:55,040
So it came off a bit harsh.

1961
01:38:55,120 --> 01:38:56,280
Do you want to save him?

1962
01:38:57,800 --> 01:38:58,960
Want to save him?

1963
01:39:00,800 --> 01:39:02,480
You can go get him in the room.

1964
01:39:02,560 --> 01:39:05,880
I'm wondering if a mentor
even has the right to get him.

1965
01:39:05,960 --> 01:39:07,600
I already sent him to fight.

1966
01:39:07,680 --> 01:39:10,760
If I go in and save him,

1967
01:39:10,840 --> 01:39:13,680
I would be spoiling him too much.

1968
01:39:13,760 --> 01:39:17,760
That was my mindset from the start.
You have to do the Black Room on your own.

1969
01:39:17,840 --> 01:39:20,000
- If you're going to cut him, do it.
- Cut him?

1970
01:39:20,080 --> 01:39:21,920
If you need to, do it.

1971
01:39:22,000 --> 01:39:23,240
I feel sorry for Mew.

1972
01:39:23,320 --> 01:39:25,920
Off wanted Mew to fight his hardest.

1973
01:39:26,000 --> 01:39:27,200
I agree with Off.

1974
01:39:27,280 --> 01:39:31,200
I don't want him to survive
just because I saved him.

1975
01:39:31,280 --> 01:39:34,320
You want to save him but you won't go in,
how would that help?

1976
01:39:34,400 --> 01:39:36,600
It's fine.
If he really fought his hardest,

1977
01:39:36,680 --> 01:39:39,280
I'll just ask for a chance
for him right here.

1978
01:39:40,160 --> 01:39:42,600
All right, I'll let them know
that everyone

1979
01:39:44,000 --> 01:39:46,520
is ready to lose them.

1980
01:39:47,920 --> 01:39:50,280
No one is taking the portfolios, right?

1981
01:39:50,800 --> 01:39:51,640
No.

1982
01:39:54,000 --> 01:39:55,360
I sent in my kid to fight.

1983
01:39:55,440 --> 01:39:58,360
Provoking me won't do any good.

1984
01:39:58,440 --> 01:40:02,160
When Pancake walked back, no one went in.

1985
01:40:02,240 --> 01:40:03,760
Oh, what about our kid?

1986
01:40:03,840 --> 01:40:06,520
If it were Mile,
I think he would've walked right in.

1987
01:40:07,800 --> 01:40:11,560
That conversation drained a lot of energy.

1988
01:40:11,640 --> 01:40:12,520
<i>Hello.</i>

1989
01:40:12,600 --> 01:40:13,960
Ananda, anything to add?

1990
01:40:14,040 --> 01:40:17,640
<i>You already talked to all mentors, right?</i>

1991
01:40:17,720 --> 01:40:18,760
Yes, I did.

1992
01:40:18,840 --> 01:40:21,760
If they want to save the members,
come get them.

1993
01:40:21,840 --> 01:40:24,240
They were ready
for the members to be eliminated.

1994
01:40:24,320 --> 01:40:28,640
I think if Mentor Mile were here,
he would've come.

1995
01:40:28,720 --> 01:40:30,120
But he's not here right now.

1996
01:40:32,520 --> 01:40:34,800
You have to put yourself first, right?

1997
01:40:34,880 --> 01:40:36,880
<i>I think they should've come out</i>
<i>to save you.</i>

1998
01:40:36,960 --> 01:40:40,520
<i>I'm not sure</i>
<i>if they're looking at this strategically.</i>

1999
01:40:40,600 --> 01:40:44,480
<i>But like I said,</i>
<i>we already gave your teams a chance.</i>

2000
01:40:44,560 --> 01:40:47,480
Pancake, it's up to you now.

2001
01:40:47,560 --> 01:40:49,560
I chose to save them.

2002
01:40:50,280 --> 01:40:52,200
And I already told the mentors.

2003
01:40:52,280 --> 01:40:53,720
No one showed up.

2004
01:40:54,680 --> 01:40:55,920
So…

2005
01:40:59,840 --> 01:41:01,760
But if it were Mile, he would've gone in.

2006
01:41:01,840 --> 01:41:04,200
- You think Mile would go in?
- I think so.

2007
01:41:04,280 --> 01:41:07,600
But I feel like
you two have the right to do it.

2008
01:41:07,680 --> 01:41:10,160
After a while, I started feeling uneasy.

2009
01:41:10,240 --> 01:41:12,640
Actually, if we have the right,
we should use it.

2010
01:41:12,720 --> 01:41:16,440
Since she opened the door for us,
we should go help.

2011
01:41:16,520 --> 01:41:17,840
Let's go in.

2012
01:41:17,920 --> 01:41:21,720
Suddenly, the two of them just stood up,
and said they were going in.

2013
01:41:23,840 --> 01:41:25,440
They were going in to help Gluf.

2014
01:41:26,800 --> 01:41:28,800
We have guests.

2015
01:41:28,880 --> 01:41:30,480
- Hello, Ananda.
- Hello.

2016
01:41:32,160 --> 01:41:33,280
<i>Oh my.</i>

2017
01:41:33,360 --> 01:41:34,640
Just figured it out?

2018
01:41:34,720 --> 01:41:36,680
Honestly, yes.

2019
01:41:36,760 --> 01:41:41,560
We want to give him a chance.
We don't want this to be his last day.

2020
01:41:41,640 --> 01:41:44,800
I feel like ultimately,
whether we're here for Mile or not,

2021
01:41:44,880 --> 01:41:49,280
I was the one who didn't give Gluf
a chance to do that campaign.

2022
01:41:49,360 --> 01:41:51,680
And I don't want
the campaign he sat out on

2023
01:41:51,760 --> 01:41:54,400
to be his last one on the show.

2024
01:41:54,480 --> 01:41:57,480
Whether he makes the Final Walk or not,

2025
01:41:57,560 --> 01:42:00,640
he deserves to show his potential.

2026
01:42:00,720 --> 01:42:02,120
Show us what you've got.

2027
01:42:02,200 --> 01:42:03,640
I will.

2028
01:42:03,720 --> 01:42:04,760
I promise.

2029
01:42:04,840 --> 01:42:07,840
<i>Make the most of this chance.</i>

2030
01:42:07,920 --> 01:42:09,400
I'll do my best.

2031
01:42:09,480 --> 01:42:11,040
<i>- See you, Gluf.</i>
- Thank you.

2032
01:42:11,120 --> 01:42:12,680
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

2033
01:42:20,680 --> 01:42:22,080
See? I was being serious.

2034
01:42:22,160 --> 01:42:24,920
And I told him to come in
if he wanted to save you.

2035
01:42:25,000 --> 01:42:27,880
Can I have one more chance, Pancake?

2036
01:42:27,960 --> 01:42:30,680
I'll prove to you that I can do it.

2037
01:42:30,760 --> 01:42:33,360
If I end up in this room again,
you can eliminate me.

2038
01:42:33,440 --> 01:42:35,160
I want to get back in there.

2039
01:42:35,240 --> 01:42:39,400
And I want to do better than before.

2040
01:42:39,480 --> 01:42:41,520
I don't care if I make the Final Walk.

2041
01:42:41,600 --> 01:42:43,360
I just want to stay.

2042
01:42:43,440 --> 01:42:46,080
And show you and Ananda

2043
01:42:46,160 --> 01:42:48,040
that I can do this too.

2044
01:42:48,120 --> 01:42:51,840
I want to see you
improve yourself more, Mew.

2045
01:42:51,920 --> 01:42:54,960
Being here on <i>The Face</i>,
you've shown a lot of things

2046
01:42:55,040 --> 01:42:57,520
and you've learned a lot too.

2047
01:43:00,040 --> 01:43:02,080
I'll repeat the three words
I said earlier.

2048
01:43:02,160 --> 01:43:05,680
Mindset, focus, and respect.

2049
01:43:06,400 --> 01:43:10,280
- I hope to see you in future projects.
- Okay.

2050
01:43:10,360 --> 01:43:11,960
- I'm sorry.
- That's okay.

2051
01:43:12,040 --> 01:43:13,760
You are not The Face.

2052
01:43:17,800 --> 01:43:19,960
I'm really not sure
why Off didn't walk in.

2053
01:43:20,040 --> 01:43:24,320
Mentor Pancake gave him a chance,
but Off was the one who didn't take it.

2054
01:43:24,400 --> 01:43:29,000
I know I might not be
as good as the others on the team.

2055
01:43:29,080 --> 01:43:32,560
But I tried my best.

2056
01:43:32,640 --> 01:43:35,320
If this is the end for me,
I'm okay with it.

2057
01:43:40,120 --> 01:43:42,280
Gluf, you're a survivor.

2058
01:43:42,360 --> 01:43:44,400
What kind of amulet do you have?

2059
01:43:44,480 --> 01:43:45,880
The Sacred Gluf?

2060
01:43:45,960 --> 01:43:48,720
This is a real miracle.

2061
01:43:48,800 --> 01:43:50,680
Who's as tough to kill as my guy?

2062
01:43:50,760 --> 01:43:53,040
How is it? Stressed?

2063
01:43:53,800 --> 01:43:54,800
A little bit.

2064
01:43:54,880 --> 01:43:58,440
I was a bit shocked
that neither mentors showed up.

2065
01:43:58,520 --> 01:44:00,440
At first, they said they wouldn't go in.

2066
01:44:00,520 --> 01:44:02,600
Then they suddenly changed their minds.

2067
01:44:02,680 --> 01:44:03,760
I was so confused.

2068
01:44:03,840 --> 01:44:06,720
This is Mentor Pancake's game.
Don't play into it.

2069
01:44:06,800 --> 01:44:08,680
I wanted to give a kid a chance.

2070
01:44:08,760 --> 01:44:11,280
If I can help him, I will.

2071
01:44:11,360 --> 01:44:13,280
Call it a game if you want, up to you.

2072
01:44:13,360 --> 01:44:15,480
I only lasted a week anyway.

2073
01:44:19,040 --> 01:44:20,440
She changed from red to black.

2074
01:44:21,600 --> 01:44:24,680
She's in a black dress.
I didn't even know when she changed.

2075
01:44:24,760 --> 01:44:27,200
It was a very long Black Room session.

2076
01:44:27,280 --> 01:44:29,160
But you changed your outfit?

2077
01:44:29,240 --> 01:44:32,240
In the last three hours,
she changed three times.

2078
01:44:32,320 --> 01:44:33,480
To be…

2079
01:44:34,200 --> 01:44:36,520
fit for sending someone home.

2080
01:44:36,600 --> 01:44:39,640
Based on performance,
Mew was better, right?

2081
01:44:39,720 --> 01:44:40,840
You sent him in.

2082
01:44:40,920 --> 01:44:43,240
Fair enough.

2083
01:44:43,320 --> 01:44:45,080
The power is in your hands anyway.

2084
01:44:45,160 --> 01:44:47,280
I use my power mindfully.

2085
01:44:47,360 --> 01:44:49,160
That's good. Nice dress.

2086
01:44:49,240 --> 01:44:50,240
Thank you.

2087
01:44:50,320 --> 01:44:51,480
It comes in two colors.

2088
01:44:51,560 --> 01:44:53,280
Mentor Off must like the wings.

2089
01:44:53,360 --> 01:44:56,320
See? She prepared everything.
She already had the red dress.

2090
01:44:56,400 --> 01:44:58,160
She comes out mourning the kid.

2091
01:44:58,240 --> 01:45:00,400
She thought this through. Definitely.

2092
01:45:00,480 --> 01:45:04,680
First, I already said if you want
to save him, go get him.

2093
01:45:05,480 --> 01:45:07,880
And this team went in to get their guy.

2094
01:45:07,960 --> 01:45:10,440
Simply put,
I'm not playing games with you.

2095
01:45:10,520 --> 01:45:12,480
I just felt I needed to finish my part.

2096
01:45:12,560 --> 01:45:16,360
Second, while Mew was in there,

2097
01:45:16,440 --> 01:45:19,000
he was still fooling around.

2098
01:45:19,080 --> 01:45:21,520
He's 18. He might just be playful.

2099
01:45:21,600 --> 01:45:23,920
It's something very easy to fix.

2100
01:45:24,000 --> 01:45:26,360
It's not like he needs to go to rehab.

2101
01:45:26,440 --> 01:45:28,360
Nothing like that. One talk is enough.

2102
01:45:28,440 --> 01:45:29,800
Are you okay, Bonus?

2103
01:45:29,880 --> 01:45:32,080
- Do you want to say anything?
- No, it's fine.

2104
01:45:32,160 --> 01:45:35,520
- "Fine" means you want to say something.
- Save it for the interview.

2105
01:45:37,400 --> 01:45:38,840
I was too scared to talk.

2106
01:45:38,920 --> 01:45:40,640
Mentor Pancake was so intimidating.

2107
01:45:40,720 --> 01:45:43,080
I want to hear it now.
What do you want to say?

2108
01:45:43,160 --> 01:45:44,680
Mew fought his best, right?

2109
01:45:44,760 --> 01:45:45,880
Yes, he did.

2110
01:45:45,960 --> 01:45:47,440
He tried his best.

2111
01:45:47,520 --> 01:45:50,720
Mercy for me, she's so intimidating.

2112
01:45:50,800 --> 01:45:54,920
I wanted to give him a chance,
but his mentor didn't come get him.

2113
01:45:55,000 --> 01:45:56,200
Okay, I understand.

2114
01:45:56,280 --> 01:45:58,960
This whole scene
is just to show off the dress.

2115
01:45:59,040 --> 01:46:00,360
Add to cart!

2116
01:46:01,160 --> 01:46:02,600
Do you want the wings?

2117
01:46:03,680 --> 01:46:06,840
I can take them off for you,
but I don't know if you'll win.

2118
01:46:07,800 --> 01:46:11,280
Five, four, three, two…

2119
01:46:13,000 --> 01:46:14,440
Donut dyed his hair.

2120
01:46:14,520 --> 01:46:17,160
He's confident. Full of charisma.

2121
01:46:17,240 --> 01:46:20,520
This is the shot the client can use.

2122
01:46:22,880 --> 01:46:24,880
Keep it cool, Leo. Keep it cool.

2123
01:46:24,960 --> 01:46:26,920
Beautiful.

2124
01:46:27,000 --> 01:46:28,680
Off is great at commentating.

2125
01:46:28,760 --> 01:46:30,600
Oh, is this a crosswalk?

2126
01:46:30,680 --> 01:46:32,520
Wow, Yaris Cross.

2127
01:46:32,600 --> 01:46:34,480
You never stop directing.

2128
01:46:34,560 --> 01:46:37,720
Now I get why boxing matches
have commentators.

2129
01:46:42,000 --> 01:46:43,960
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
